INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (243, 'Missing Text', NULL, NULL, 'Auf meiner Suche nach Moosproben stie? ich auf den Schauplatz eines blutigen Kampfes. Der Vilefinstamm der Murlocs war von einer marodierenden Bande Gnolle belagert worden. überall lagen tote Gnolle und Murlocs herum. Als ich an einer solchen zerschundenen Murlocleiche vorbeikam, fiel mir ein merkwürdig verh?rteter Tumor auf, der aus einer der Wunden wuchs. Ich begann rasch mit der Untersuchung des Tumors und stellte fest, dass er ?hnliche Eigenschaften aufwies wie das Moos, das ich sammelte. Leider fand ich keine weiteren Tumore.', '比索·埃斯沙德大人：$B$B 遵照您的指令，我派遣这个$c来为您效力。$B$B $g他:她;非常可靠，而且听从指挥，在对付天灾军队的过程中证明了自己的实力，所以我选择$g他:她;来协助您完成任务。$B$B 祝您安好，$B - 执政官塞弗伦', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Собирая образцы мха, я случайно стал свидетелем сцены кровавой битвы. Клан мурлоков Коварного Плавника подвергся нападению мародерствующих банд гноллов. Трупы и гноллов, и мурлоков были разбросаны по всему полю боя. Когда я проходил мимо растерзанного тела мурлока, я заметил странно затвердевшую опухоль, выступающую из раны. Когда я начал изучать ее, стало ясно, что похожие свойства я обнаружил у мха, который собирал. К сожалению, больше я не смог больше найти ни одной опухоли.');
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (44, 'Missing Text', NULL, 'Je connais personnellement Edwin VanCleef depuis toujours, je vous assure que l\'avoir comme ennemi est une mauvaise idée. C\'est un ami d\'enfance, et je lui ai personnellement appris les voies des Ténèbres, au cas où il envisagerait un jour une carrière à mes côtés. Si VanCleef rejoint la Confrérie des Défias, que la Lumière ait pitié de nous.\n\nMaître Mathias Shaw\nGuilde des Assassins de Hurlevent', 'Ich kenne Edwin van Cleef nun schon mein Leben lang und ich würde jedem davon abraten, sich ihn zum Feind zu machen. Denn seht, wir waren schon als Kinder Freunde, und ich habe ihn pers?nlich im Schattenkampf unterwiesen, in der Hoffnung, er würde eines Tages eine Laufbahn an meiner Seite in Erw?gung ziehen. Sollte van Cleef inzwischen tats?chlich der Bruderschaft der Defias vorstehen, m?ge das Licht Euren Seelen gn?dig sein.$B$BMeister Mathias Shaw$BAuftragsm?rdergilde von Sturmwind', '亲自已知昭vancleef我的整个生命,我可以告诉你,他面临着一个敌人,这是一个相当艰巨的任务.你看,他是我童年的朋友,我亲自训练他的方法响声,以为有一天他可能会考虑职业,我旁边.如果是vancleef标题起来迪菲亚信使兄弟,可轻保佑我们的灵魂.大师马蒂亚斯逸夫暴风刺客的会馆', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Зная Эдвина ван Клифа всю свою жизнь, я могу сказать, что видеть в нем своего врага мне неприятно. Понимаете, он был моим другом детства, и я лично наставлял его в магии Теней, надеясь, что однажды он будет работать вместе со мной. Если ван Клиф стоит во главе Братства Справедливости, то да помилует Свет наши души!\r\n\r\nМастер Матиас Шоу\r\nГильдия убийц Штормграда');
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (27, 'Missing Text', NULL, 'Bonjour William,\n\nVoilà des années que nous n\'avons pas parlé, et j\'ai bon espoir que vous et votre frère vous portez bien, ainsi que vos affaires.\n\nJe dois vous demander une faveur, William. Pour faire court, mon petit-fils Tommy Joe s\'est épris de la jeune Maybell Maclure. Et bien qu\'ils s\'adorent, nos familles, ma foi, nos familles s\'affrontent depuis des années.', 'Mein lieber William, Jahre ist es her, seit wir uns das letzte Mal gesprochen haben. Ich hoffe inst?ndig, Euch und Eurem Bruder geht es gut und Eure Apothekerdienste sind gefragt. Nun muss ich Euch um einen Gefallen bitten, William. Ich will keine langen Worte machen. Mein Enkel Tommy Joe hat sein Herz an die junge Maybell Maclure verloren. Und sie k?nnten sich innig lieben, wenn unsere Familien... tja, unsere Familien leben seit Jahren in Fehde.', '威廉你好,它的几年里,因为我们已经说过,但我相信你和你的兄弟都很好,你药师的兴盛.我必须浼你,威廉.总之,我的孙子托米乔已经失去了他的心,年轻梅贝尔苦瓜.虽然他们仰慕对方… …我们的家庭,良好的家庭已争吵多年.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Здравствуй, Вильям !Мы уже много лет не разговариваем, но я надеюсь, что у вас с братом все в порядке и что ваша аптека процветает. У меня к тебе просьба, Вильям. В общем, мой внук Томми Джо влюблен в юную Мейбелл Маклюр. Они друг в друге души не чают, но наши семьи... Конечно, наши семьи враждуют уже много лет...');
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (2350, 'This intact pteradon skeleton was recovered from the remote Un\'Goro Crater. Based on the skeletal structure, it is clear that this specific genus has not yet been encountered. This skeleton could have been preserved for any number of centuries beneath the region\'s rich soil.', NULL, 'Ce squelette intact de ptéradon a été découvert dans le lointain cratère d\'Un\'Goro. D\'après la structure du squelette, il apparaît clairement que cette espèce n\'a encore jamais été rencontrée. Ce squelette pourrait avoir été préservé pendant des siècles dans le riche sol de la région.', 'Dieses unversehrte Pteradonskelett wurde im entlegenen Krater von Un\'Goro geborgen. Dem Aufbau des Skeletts l?sst sich genau entnehmen, dass diese spezielle Unterart noch nicht entdeckt wurde. Das Skelett k?nnte Jahrhunderte unter dem fruchtbaren Boden der Region erhalten geblieben sein.', '这块完整的翼手龙骨骼是从遥远的安戈洛环形山运回来的。根据骨架的结构判断，其特殊的基因还从未改变过。这块骨架在该地区的特殊土壤中可以保存近乎无限长的时间。 ', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Этот скелет птерадона был найден в Кратере Ун\'Горо. Глядя на его структуру, мы можем сделать вывод, что перед нами новый, неизвестный науке вид. Скелет мог пролежать под слоем богатой почвы Ун\'Горо много столетий.');
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (10000, 'True to their nature, the Goblins have always scavenged for artifacts and relics that would make them profit. It was because of his greed that the Trade Prince of the Venture Trade Company sent a group of Goblins far into the depths of the Stonetalon Mountains. It is said that a shadowy figure sold them a tip about a grave that must never be open yet one that also holds a way to quickly amass gold.\n\nIf it was anyone else but a goblin, they would properly turn tail and not list a word, yet when it comes to gold, a goblin is easily persuaded.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '忠于他们的天性，地精一直在寻找能让他们获利的文物和遗物。正是因为贪婪，风险投资贸易公司派遣了一组地精前往石爪山脉深处。据说，一个神秘的人向他们出售了一个关于一个绝不能被打开的坟墓的线索，然而这个坟墓也同时提供了迅速积累财富的方法。\n\n如果不是地精，其他人可能会立刻逃跑，不吭声，然而当涉及到金子时，地精很容易被说服。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (10001, 'Their task proved to be a harsh one, many only found their own death in those Mountains, either at the hands of the savage wildlife, the Night Elves which were guarding the tomb or at the means of their own creation.\n\nAs they slowly progressed to the tomb, some succumbed to fear, there was something dark in there. For a few of them it was not worth wasting their life for someone else\'s gold, so with the little means they had a group of them take flight and aim for Durotar.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '事实证明，他们的任务是艰巨的，许多人只能在这些山脉中死去，要么死在野蛮的野生动物、守卫坟墓的暗夜精灵手中，要么死于他们自己的创造物。\n\n随着他们缓慢地前进，一些人屈服于恐惧，坟墓里有一些黑暗的东西。对于其中一些人来说，不值得为别人的金子而浪费自己的生命，所以他们中的一群人带着他们所能凑齐的一点点资源飞往杜隆塔尔。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (10002, '<Your new friend looks a little dehydrated.>', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<你的新朋友看起来有点脱水。>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (10010, 'Led by the former Foreman, Nert Blastentom, the rebellious Goblins crashed their plane close to the town of Razor Hill. It was there that Nert had an acquaintance that would prove useful in their plan to hide under the Horde\'s banner.\n\nThe local chef was someone Nert met in the past in Ratchet when Nert was but a lowly merchant who attempted to sell the orc counterfeit merchandise.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '在前工头纳特·布拉斯滕托姆的带领下，叛逆的哥布林在剃刀岭附近坠毁了他们的飞机。 正是在那里，纳特结识了一位熟人，他们的计划中将会用到这个熟人，以躲避部落的旗帜下。\n\n当地的厨师是纳特过去在棘齿城遇到的人，当时纳特只是一个试图出售兽人假冒商品的卑微商人。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (10011, 'With the efforts of the few Goblins that followed him, Nert hunted the local boars for a mischievous bribery he\'d offer the guards to allow them passage through their lands.\n\nThanks to his employee, Agnes, who had a very special bag of spices, the orcish chef managed to turn a simple meal into a feast.\n\nBeing successful in their plot to bribe the local guards, the Goblins were allowed safe passage through the Horde\'s lands and a protection they would most likely enjoy.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '在跟随他的少数地精的努力下，纳特猎杀了当地的野猪，他向守卫提供恶作剧的贿赂，允许他们通过他们的土地。\n\n感谢他的雇员艾格尼丝有一袋非常特别的香料，兽人厨师成功地将一顿简单的饭菜变成了一场盛宴。\n\n地精贿赂当地守卫的阴谋成功后，他们被允许安全通过部落的土地，并得到他们有可能享受的保护。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (10020, 'Knowing that he\'d have to prove to the Horde that he and his former employees are capable of aiding the cause, Nert traveled to Ratchet to meet with Gazlowe. Gazlowe had connections inside the Horde and he\'d be a great token for Nert to use against those that would have them exiled, or in the worst case, killed because of the Venture Trade Company\'s reputation.\n\nGazlowe didn\'t agree at first. He\'d take some days to consider whether to help these refugees or not. In the end he reached the conclusion that the Horde lacks a Goblin\'s touch and called for Nert making him the proposition of forming an union that any Goblin who would decide to be part of the Horde could join.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '纳特知道他必须向部落证明他和他的前雇员有能力为这项事业提供帮助，因此他前往棘齿城与加兹鲁维会面。 加兹鲁维在部落内部有联系，他将是纳特用来对付那些可能会因为风险探险公司的声誉而放逐他们，甚至在最糟糕的情况下杀死他们的人的一张重要牌。\n\n加兹鲁维一开始并不同意。 他需要几天的时间来考虑是否要帮助这些难民。 最后他得出的结论是部落缺乏地精的接触，并呼吁纳特向他提出组建一个联盟的提议，任何决定加入部落的哥布林都可以加入。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (10021, 'Nert was puzzled by this but saw a great opportunity, and decided to go along with the plan. And so a new union was born, claiming the name of Durotar Labor Union, this new group of Goblins would accept Goblins from all around the world that would wish to join the Horde.\n\nClaiming the title of Grand Taskmaster of the Durotar Labor Union, Nert would soon have the opportunity to prove his people\'s worth to the Horde.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '纳特对此感到困惑，但他看到了一个巨大的机会，决定跟随这个计划。于是，一个新的联盟诞生了，以杜隆塔尔劳工联盟的名义，这个新的地精团体将接纳来自世界各地希望加入部落的地精。\n\n作为杜隆塔尔劳工联盟的大任务大师，纳特很快将有机会向部落证明他的人民的价值。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (10030, 'With the Durotar Labor Union founded and Gazlowe vouching for them before the Warchief of the Horde, all Nert had to do was wait for a task. He left some of his men in Durotar to aid with the various needs, while others were sent through Kalimdor to raise their reputation. As for him and a small group, they\'d settle in the Dustallow Marsh, giving birth to a new Horde settlement called Mudsprocket.\n\nFor a few months, the Goblins had to adapt with the harsh environment, not only were they assaulted by the local wildlife but they\'d even have to craft meticulous tools to push back the spawns of Onyxia.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '随着杜隆塔尔劳工联盟的成立，加兹鲁维在部落酋长面前为他们作证，纳特所要做的就是等待任务。他在杜隆塔尔留下了一些人，协助满足各种需求，而其他人则被派遣到卡利姆多各地提高声誉。至于他和一个小团队，他们将在尘泥沼泽定居，建立起一个名为“泥链镇”的新部落定居点。\n\n在接下来的几个月里，地精们不得不适应严酷的环境，他们不仅受到当地野生动物的攻击，甚至还不得不精心制作工具来击退奥妮克希亚的产卵。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (10031, 'In the end, after waiting patiently, the Warchief issued the Durotar Labor Union to create a port close to the Horde\'s capital, Orgrimmar. The port would take immense work but was it not for the oil resources in the vicinity of Bladefist Bay, it would\'ve taken them even longer.\n\nAfter much dedication and much, much labor, the port which would soon become the main city of the Goblins was complete. Nert would name it Sparkwater Port, and with that he\'d paint his and the Durotar Labor Union\'s name into the Horde\'s history.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '最终，在耐心等待之后，大酋长下令杜隆塔尔劳工联盟在部落首都奥格瑞玛附近建立一个港口。这个港口需要付出巨大的努力，但要不是在刃拳海湾附近的石油资源，它们可能需要更长的时间。\n\n经过长时间的投入和辛勤的劳动，这个港口很快就成为了地精的主要城市。纳特将其命名为“火花港”，借此将他和杜隆塔尔劳工联盟的名字铭刻在了部落的历史中。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50065, 'The Professor told me that he has taught other people to disguise themselves. He has not told me where they are but he has given me a list indicating what their disguises are, I must go and look for them in the places where they have been able to infiltrate and they may want to teach me too.$B$B· Defias Footpad$B· Dark Iron Dwarf$B· Southsea Pirate$B· Dalaran Wizard$B· Stonesplinter Trogg$B· Syndicate Highwayman', NULL, NULL, NULL, '教授告诉我，他已经教会了其他人如何伪装自己。他没有告诉我他们在哪里，但他给了我一张清单，上面列出了他们的伪装，我必须去那些他们成功渗透过的地方寻找他们，他们可能也想教我。$B$B¡¤ 亡命劫匪（Defias Footpad）$B$B¡¤ 黑铁矮人（Dark Iron Dwarf）$B$B¡¤南海海盗（Southsea Pirate）$B$B¡¤ 达拉然巫师（Dalaran Wizard）$B$B¡¤ 石拳穴居人（Stonesplinter Trogg）$B$B¡¤ 辛迪加高级成员', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50066, 'Red button! Starts the engine, of course! Levers for stearing.\n\nObviously don\'t hit any rocks on the way. Hit the landmarks to get points and smear down these gnomes! If you happend to experience explosion of the race car and have no insurance then your belongings will be passed to Kruzak and Goblin Engineering team.\n\nThanks for running the race car durability crash test for us!\n\nYou\'re awesome!', NULL, NULL, NULL, '红色按钮！当然是启动引擎！操纵杆用来控制方向。\n\n当然，在途中不要撞到岩石。撞击地标可以得分，也可以将这些侏儒撞落！\n\n如果你不幸经历了赛车爆炸，而且没有保险，你的财物将被传递给克鲁扎克和地精工程团队。\n\n感谢你为我们进行赛车耐久性碰撞测试！\n\n你真棒！', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50067, 'Red button! Starts the engine, of course! Levers for stearing.\n\nObviously don\'t hit any rocks on the way. Hit the landmarks to get points and smear down these goblins! If you happend to experience explosion of the race car and have no insurance then your belongings will be passed to Garry Crashbash and Gnome Engineering team.\n\nThanks for running the race car durability crash test for us!\n\nYou\'re awesome!', NULL, NULL, NULL, '红色按钮！当然是启动引擎！操纵杆用来控制方向。\n\n当然，在途中不要撞到岩石。撞击地标可以得分，也可以将这些地精撞倒！\n\n如果你不幸经历了赛车爆炸，而且没有保险，你的财物将被传递给加里·碰撞和侏儒工程团队。\n\n感谢你为我们进行赛车耐久性碰撞测试！\n\n你真棒！', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50080, 'SHIMMERING FLATS — the sounds of desert creatures and sandstorms have been replaced. Gone is the clattering of scorpids, evicted from their natural home by the powerful roar of engines. As engineers from around the world congregate to create the fastest machine ever to traverse these once open plains, Gadgetzan Times was given the unique opportunity to talk with some of the pit crew.\n\r\n\"What we are trying to achieve here is not simply a land speed record.\" G.T. was told by Gregor Fizzwuzz, assistant to the great Brassbolts brothers, \"I mean sure, we want to build something that will be remembered through history as a fine piece of Gnomish Engineering, but more importantly; we want to beat those Goblins!\"', NULL, NULL, NULL, '闪光平原 — 沙漠生物和沙尘暴的声音已被替代。蝎子人的叮当声不再存在，它们被引擎的强大轰鸣声赶出了它们的自然栖息地。作为来自世界各地的工程师聚集在一起，旨在创造出有史以来在这些曾经广袤平原上奔驰的最快的机器，加基兹坦时报得到了与一些维修人员交谈的独特机会。\n\n\"我们在这里试图实现的不仅仅是陆地速度记录。\" 格雷戈·菲兹乌兹对加吉兹坦时报表示，他是伟大的布拉斯博尔兄弟的助手，\"我是说，当然，我们希望建造出一件被历史铭记的美妙侏儒工程作品，但更重要的是，我们想要击败那些地精！\"', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50081, 'It\'s true that the Gnomish engineers have progressed far in the development of their \'racers\' but following them step for step technologically have been the Goblins who know a money-maker when they see one.\n\r\n\"The Gnomes never build anything that works,\" remarks Ed Sprockett, one of the goblin crew-workers, \"They spend so much time tinkering and fiddling with the little things that they forget that they are working on a larger project. The smaller components that regulate the internal lighting and the cushions on their seats may be good ideas but if the \'thing\' never moves, it\'s a complete waste of time.\"', NULL, NULL, NULL, '的确，侏儒工程师在他们的“赛车”开发方面取得了很大的进展，但在技术上紧随其后的是那些看到赚钱机会的地精。\n\n\"侏儒从不制造真正能用的东西，\" 地精船员之一艾德·斯普洛克特评论道，\"他们花费太多时间去修修补补一些小东西，以至于忘记了他们正在做一个更大的项目。调节内部照明和座椅靠垫的较小部件可能是好主意，但如果那个\'东西\'从未动过，那就是完全浪费时间。\"', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50082, 'The Gnomes and the Goblins have been out here in the Shimmering Flats for a long time trying to build a better speed racer than each other. So how much progress has been made?\n\r\nG.T. tried to pose this question to one of the Brassbolts brothers but they were surprisingly reluctant to speak. Instead, young Fizzwuzz spoke up again:\n\r\n\"Well. We\'ve come a long way from mechanostriders that\'s for sure!\" he laughs, \"There\'s still a lot of work to do but we feel that greats strides have been taken and we are close to a breakthrough.\"', NULL, NULL, NULL, '侏儒和地精在闪光平原呆了很长时间，试图建造比对方更好的速度赛车。那么，他们取得了多大的进展呢？\n\n加基兹坦时报试图向布拉斯博尔兄弟之一提出这个问题，但他们出奇地不愿意说话。相反，年轻的菲兹乌兹再次发言：\n\n“好吧。我们已经远离机械陆行鸟了，这是肯定的！” 他笑着说：“还有很多工作要做，但我们觉得已经取得了长足的进步，我们即将取得突破。”', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50083, 'He took this opportunity to give G.T. a sneak peak at the marvelous progression away from the mechanostrider which was the Gnomish racer.\n\r\n\"Sure, it looks like a water tower crossed with a zeppelin,\" he said with a nervous smile, \"but it has major changes to its basic structure which are going to make it much better.\"\n\r\n\"The stripe will make it go faster!\"\n\r\nFor the time being, it seems that Goblin technology has little to fear from the Gnomes.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '他趁此机会向加基兹坦时报展示了从侏儒赛车（机械陆行鸟）中奇妙的进展。\n\n\"当然，它看起来像是一个与齐柏林飞艇杂交的水塔，\" 他带着紧张的微笑说道，\"但它在基本结构上有了重大的变化，这将使它变得更好。\"\n\n\"条纹会让它跑得更快！\"\n\n就目前而言，地精技术似乎没有什么值得惧怕侏儒的。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50085, 'Blood be red, mon\r\nTroll skin be blue\r\nIf you be readin\' dis\r\nI put a hex on you', NULL, NULL, NULL, '血液是红色的，伙计\n巨魔皮肤是蓝色的\n如果你正在读这个\n我对你施了一种咒术', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50086, 'Berserking glow red\r\nHeartsong glow blue\r\nNobody enchant me\r\nDe way dat you do', NULL, NULL, NULL, '狂暴发出红光\n心曲闪耀蓝光\n没有人像你一样\n以你的方式附魔我', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50087, 'Blood be red mon,\r\nThe sky above Zandalar be blue\r\nIf dis got you in da mood,\r\nCome get my voodoo', NULL, NULL, NULL, '血液是红色的，伙计，\n赞达拉上空的天空是蓝色的，\n如果这让你心情愉快，\n来体验我的巫毒吧。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50088, 'Roses are red\r\nIris\' are indigo\r\nAll I can say when I look at you\r\nIs Taz\'dingo', NULL, NULL, NULL, '玫瑰是红色的，\n鸢尾花是靛蓝的，\n当我看着你时我只能说\n是塔兹丁戈。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50100, 'Before you reap your harvest you sowing seeds and foster them with care.\n\nFirst and perhaps an easiest one to start with will be Pumpkins. You will need some of those Pumpkin Seeds from ripe enough Pumpkin you can find. Nearly every farmer in the fields gather only ripe Pumpkins and extract new grown seeds for the next harvest.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '在你收获之前，你会播种种子并用关爱培育它们。\n\n首先，也许是最容易开始的，将是南瓜。你会需要一些成熟的南瓜中提取出的南瓜种子。几乎每个农民在田间都只收集成熟的南瓜，并提取新长出的种子用于下一次收获。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50101, 'Second would be very similar, however a bit more complicated to tend to - watermelons. To grow some you will need seeds as well and the place to find them is very similar. Some farmers specialize on that sweet giant berries and grow only them. They are not many and very well known across all Eastern Kingdoms.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '第二个将会非常相似，但稍微复杂一些——西瓜。要种植一些西瓜，你同样需要种子，而找到这些种子的地方也非常相似。一些农民专门种植这些甜蜜的巨大浆果，只种植它们。他们并不多，但在整个东部王国都很有名。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50102, 'More than interesting and absolutely another story is mushrooms. Yes, you can grow these too! Alas, mushroom spores are pretty special and differ greatly. You will have to search for those who have dedicated their lifetime for such study. Mushrooms grow well if tended right. Sometimes they grow as pest and should be avoided at all costs. Be very careful.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '更有趣且绝对是另一种故事的是蘑菇。是的，你也可以种植它们！然而，蘑菇孢子非常特殊且各不相同。你必须寻找那些将一生献给此类研究的人。如果适当地照料，蘑菇会茁壮成长。有时它们会像害虫一样生长，应该尽一切努力避免。务必非常小心。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50103, 'Last thing you\'d be able to grow on your own with the same technique is the Mountain Berry seeds which are known to grow on natural hills, alas, the world is filled with hills not every hill is good enough for these berries. Not far from Durnhold Keep I had my chance to trade with one of the Wildhammers and I\'ve managed to buy a hefty amount of such seeds. No idea where he got them, but all seeds were in great shape, fertile and fresh, so I can only assume it\'s not too far from that spot. You will have to search. Be careful there, area is dense with fierce wildlife and gruesome monsters should you stride too far.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '最后一种你可以使用相同技术自己种植的是山莓种子，它们通常生长在自然山丘上。然而，世界上充满了山丘，并不是每个山丘都适合这些浆果的生长。在邓巴德堡附近，我有机会与一位蛮锤矮人进行交易，我成功购买了大量这种种子。虽然不知道他是从哪里得到的，但所有的种子都保存得很好，肥沃且新鲜，所以我只能假设距离那个地点不会太远。你需要去寻找。但请小心，该地区充斥着凶猛的野生动物和可怕的怪物，如果走得太远，可能会遭遇危险。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50104, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50105, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50500, 'To Magus Bromley\n\nThe Ley-Shard\'s you sent me were magnificent to behold. The way in which the Highborne have channeled magic has always been interesting to me, and shall advance the research of Dalaran well.\n\nThough, that is not why you have sent them. After some studying of the Ley-Shard\'s I have found traces of a foreign magic lingering upon the crystals and exhausting their magical potency. This all but confirms there is tampering going on within the region of Azshara as you have thought.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '致魔导师布罗姆利\n\n您寄给我的魔晶碎片真是令人惊叹。高等精灵引导魔法的方式一直让我深感兴趣，它将有助于达拉然的研究进展。\n\n然而，您寄送它们的目的并非如此。经过对这些魔晶碎片的研究，我发现上面留有一种外来魔法的痕迹，正在逐渐耗尽它们的魔法力量。这几乎可以确定，正如您所想的那样，艾萨拉地区正在发生干预行为。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50501, 'Whilst, I have given you good news, I must also deliver bad. The foreign magic is that of a Draconic nature, we have many examples and studies done, so I am completely certain. The only group operating in that region would be the Blue Dragonflight. The reason they would have to do so I cannot give you, but it is their magic lingering upon the Shard\'s. I wish you luck in resolving this, and advise you look for outside help, rather then tackling the Dragonflight on your own.\n\nA friend, Archmage Ansirem Runeweaver of Dalaran.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '虽然我给您带来了好消息，但我也必须传递坏消息。这种外来的魔法是龙类的性质，我们有许多例子和研究，所以我非常确定。在该地区操作的唯一团体将是蓝龙军团。他们为什么要这样做，我无法告诉您，但是这是他们的魔法留在了魔晶碎片上。祝您在解决这个问题时好运，并建议您寻求外部帮助，而不是单独对抗蓝龙军团。\n\n您的朋友，达拉然的大法师安希瑞姆·符文图腾。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50502, 'Hello there Bromley! I sent the bearer of this box with the supplies you needed! Sorry for taking so long, there is a lot of danger between you and us! Thanks again for the magical help you\'ve given us, you certainly advanced our projects!\n\nGigno Flaxwhisker of the Flaxwhisker Front.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '你好，布罗姆利！我派遣了携带这个盒子的人带去了你需要的物资！抱歉耽误了一些时间，你和我们之间有很多危险！再次感谢你为我们提供的魔法帮助，你确实推动了我们的项目发展！\n\n弗拉克斯惠斯克家族前线的吉格诺·弗拉克斯惠斯克。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50503, 'To Gigno.\n\nThanks for the supplies, it is good to hear you and your gnomes are in good health and still advancing the great field of science. I have news of your robot that I helped craft. Whilst I was visiting the Naga of the Rethress Sanctum I noticed it upon the coast. They have seemed to leave it alone, being that the robot is malfunctioning and inactive. I hope this information is helpful to you, and I wish you continued luck\n\nMagus Bromley , Kirin Tor.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '致吉格诺：\n\n感谢提供的物资，很高兴听到你和你的侏儒们身体健康，并且在继续推进伟大的科学领域。关于我帮助制作的机器人，我有一些消息。在我访问雷瑟斯圣所的纳迦时，我注意到它就在海岸边。他们似乎没有去碰它，可能是因为机器人发生了故障，停止了运作。希望这个信息对你有所帮助，祝你继续好运。\n\n魔导师布罗姆利，肯瑞托。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50504, 'Recon over Azshara 22.03 04:22-05:55\n\nRecon over Winterspring 01.04 14:33-15:03\n\nRecon over Blue Dragons in Azshara 06.04 15:22-15:51\n\nRecon over Icepoint Rock north of Winterspring 07.04 05:22-09:31', NULL, NULL, NULL, '艾萨拉侦察 22.03 04:22-05:55\n\n冬泉谷侦察 01.04 14:33-15:03\n\n艾萨拉蓝龙侦察 06.04 15:22-15:51\n\n侦察冬泉谷以北的冰点岩 07.04 05:22-09:31', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50505, 'To Tinkmaster Overspark of Gnomeregan.\n\nI have not recieved word from you in countless months, our situation is growing more unstable with the death of crew members and the lack of supplies! I have enlisted the carrier of this report to send you this letter due to not being able to myself. I demand to know where support is from Gnomeregan, or why we have not heard from anyone in so long.\n\nI would also request a backup Tinkerspark Transponder with haste, we lost ours long ago from a naga raid.\n\nGigno Flaxwhisker!', NULL, NULL, NULL, '致便携工程师波弗斯巴克，来自诺莫瑞根。\n\n数月来，我未从您那里收到任何消息，我们的情况越来越不稳定，船员死亡，物资匮乏！由于我自己无法传信，我已请本报告的携带者将此信送给您。我要求知道诺莫瑞根的支援在哪里，为何我们这么长时间都未收到任何消息。\n\n我还想请求尽快提供备用的工程师标识传输器，我们很久以前就在纳迦的袭击中失去了它。\n\n吉格诺·弗拉克斯惠斯克！', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50506, 'To Gigno Flaxwhisker of Flaxwhisker Front.\n\nIt brings me great heartbreak to inform you on the dire circumstances regarding Gnomeregan. The city is destroyed, and what once was is no longer any more! After the invasions of troggs the tunnels became irradiated beyond belief.\n\nMany of our kin still remain there, badly affected by the irradiation and turned into vile leper gnomes! The rest of us who escaped created Tinker Town in Ironforge, it is currently our new home. I have enclosed in the letter coins enough for you to travel home, find whatever means you can, and return to Tinker Town.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '致弗拉克斯惠斯克前线的吉格诺·弗拉克斯惠斯克。\n\n我很难过地告诉您诺莫瑞根的严峻情况。城市已经毁灭，曾经的一切都不复存在！在穴居人入侵之后，隧道受到了令人难以置信的辐射。\n\n我们的许多同胞仍然留在那里，受到辐射的影响严重，变成了邪恶的麻风侏儒！我们逃离的余部在铁炉堡建立了修补匠镇，那是我们目前的新家。我在信中附上了足够您回家的硬币，尽您所能找到合适的方式，回到修补匠镇。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50507, 'To Watch Paladin Janathos\n\nMe and my company were attacked heading to the east by Lost One\'s of the Fallow Sanctuary. Many of the others were killed and our supplies were taken, I was able to escape and have been barely surviving in a camp I created. I will return soon, when I have gained some rest.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '给看守圣骑士贾纳托斯：\n\n我和我的同伴在前往东部的途中遭到了落锤圣殿的失落者的袭击。许多人被杀害，我们的供应品被抢走，我设法逃脱，并在一个我建立的营地里勉强存活。我会很快回来，等我休息好了。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50508, 'Hello Karl, it has been a long time, and I wanted to reach out in assurance that I am still alive, and kicking. It has been forever since we have seen, and I am eager to see you once again.\n\nAfter departing from Kul Tiras, the fleet spent an extended amount of time at sea. As of recently we were attacked and the ship was destroyed and now we currently reside on the Isle of Lapidis off the coast of Stranglethorn Vale. When the ship is repaired, I will be returning home, and will stop by to say hello like old times.\n\nYour Older Brother Arnold.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '你好，卡尔，很久不见了，我想通过这封信向你确保我还活着，仍然精力充沛。我们已经很久没有见面了，我渴望再次见到你。\n\n离开库尔提拉斯后，舰队在海上停留了相当长的时间。最近我们遭到了袭击，船被摧毁，现在我们暂时驻扎在拉皮迪斯岛，位于荆棘谷海岸。当船修好后，我会回家，并会像过去一样，过来和你打个招呼。\n\n你的哥哥，阿诺德。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50509, 'Little brother, it has been an eternity since we have seen one another. I am currently stranded on an island called Lapidis off the coast of Stranglethorn Vale near the south seas with others in the fleet. We call this place home, and have for a while now, and are repairing our ship.\n\nWhen repairs are done, I will be stopping to see you and Karl. I look forward to this day very well, and hope you are doing good.\n\nYour Older Brother Arnold.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '弟弟，我们已经很久没有见面了。我目前被困在一个名为拉皮迪斯的岛屿上，位于荆棘谷的海岸，靠近南海，与舰队中的其他人一起。我们已经把这个地方当作家，修理我们的船已经有一段时间了。\n\n当修好了，我会停下来看你和卡尔。我非常期待那一天，希望你过得不错。\n\n你的哥哥，阿诺德。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50510, 'To Loruk Foreststrider\n\nYour suspicions seem to have been correct, it would seem as if something horrid lurks within the very air. The furbolg who once seemed so very friendly have been turned evil and are hostile upon sight.\n\nThe land itself is beginning to wither and fade. Large craters have dotted the landscape and most of the wildlife seems to be in a similar frenzy to that of the Furbolg. I was unable to see the one who supposedly is the keeper of this place as the area is to dangerous to travel alone.\n\nSomething terrible has happened here, and something must be done.\n\nFeran Strongwind.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '给洛鲁克·林行者\n\n你的怀疑似乎是正确的，似乎有一些可怕的事情隐藏在空气中。那些曾经看起来友好的熊怪现在变得邪恶，一看到就会攻击。\n\n土地本身开始枯萎和消失。大的陨石坑点缀着整个大地，大部分野生生物似乎都陷入了类似于熊怪的狂热状态。我无法见到那个据说是这个地方的守护者，因为这个区域太危险，独自旅行不安全。\n\n这里发生了可怕的事情，必须采取行动。\n\n费兰·强风', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50511, 'To Fandral Staghelm, Arch Druid\n\nThere is corruption present within Ashenvale, with each passing day the wildlife grows more aggresive and the furbolg more brazen. They are no longer our friends within the forest and have taken to arms against any who dare show themselves.\n\nWithin their abandoned villages lay trinkets of a dark intent, rocks carved in crude runes, and the very sap in which they indulge has been tainted.\n\nThey have lost their way, and we must find a way to solve this issue, lest all of the forest be lost to such madness.\n\nFaldan Moonshatter', NULL, NULL, NULL, '致范达尔·鹿盔、大德鲁伊\n\n灰谷内存在着腐败现象，野生动物日渐变得更具攻击性，而熊怪也变得更加肆无忌惮。 他们不再是我们在森林里的朋友，并拿起武器对抗任何敢于现身的人。\n\n在他们废弃的村庄里，散布着带有黑暗意图的小玩意儿，岩石上刻有粗糙的符文，他们所沉迷的树液也被污染了。\n\n他们迷失了方向，我们必须找到解决这个问题的方法，以免整个森林都因这种疯狂而消失。\n\n法尔丹·碎月者', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50512, '$N, it was my pleasure to hear that a recruit shows passion for the art of hunting.\n\nAlthough in life we would’ve never considered ourselves as great of a marksman as either the dwarves or the high elves we took our pride for the love we carried for the wilds, befriending animals into long loyal companions and feeling the rhythm and the call of nature in every gust of wind, every groan of the river was something that brought upmost joy into our lives.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '$N，很高兴听到一位新兵对狩猎艺术充满热情。\n\n尽管在生活中，我们从未将自己视为像矮人或高等精灵那样出色的射手，但我们为自己对荒野的热爱而感到自豪，将动物变成了忠诚的长期伙伴，感受着自然的韵律和呼唤，每一阵风的吹拂，每一声河水的响动都给我们的生活带来了极大的快乐。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50513, 'Adapting to nature was one of our greatest and most noble of goals, yet as we’ve experimented with what comes after a restless death, we can no longer adapt to nature, it seems that nature itself will need to adapt to us. Meet me by the graveyard, it’s there I shall teach you of my past experiences and a few tricks for you to survive and claim your vengeance against the Lich King.\n\nFor the Banshee Queen, for the Forsaken.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '适应自然是我们最伟大、最崇高的目标之一，然而当我们尝试着从不安宁的死亡之后找到出路时，我们再也无法适应自然，似乎是自然需要适应我们。在墓地见我，我会在那里告诉你我过去的经历，并教你一些技巧，帮助你在与巫妖王的战斗中生存下来并报仇。\n\n为了女妖之王，为了被遗忘者。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50514, 'The temperance of great metal and the emboldening with dark magic is the key to much of our work. To channel such magic within the runes of blade takes vast amount of resources plentiful to our kin.\n\nDark Runes must be etched upon the surface of the blade, and heated to extreme temperature, these runes must be placed at the very center of the blade itself, lest the powers be diminished.\n\nEnchanted Leather must be bound and wrapped about the hilt, as to secure the magical potency and balance of the weapon itself.\n\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, '伟大的金属之中蕴含着克制与黑暗魔法的力量，这是我们工作的关键。要将这种魔法引导到剑的符文中，需要大量的资源，这对我们的同族来说是丰富充足的。\n\n必须在刀刃的表面上刻上黑暗符文，并将其加热到极高的温度，这些符文必须放置在刀刃的中心位置，以免力量减弱。\n\n附魔皮革必须绑定并包裹在剑柄上，以确保武器本身的魔法效果和平衡。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50515, 'These are the first techniques required to master for the true creation of the Runeblade, and if one is to master our great magic, then they too can learn such methods.\n\nFor those who have been loyal, and wish to seek such knowledge, they must seek me out at my study upon this mortal world. You can find me within the ravine, lackered in shadow, accompanied by those who I call servants.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '这些是真正创造符文之刃所需的第一步技术，如果有人要掌握我们伟大的魔法，那么他们也可以学会这些方法。\n\n对于那些忠诚并希望寻求这种知识的人，他们必须在这个凡人世界上找到我。你可以在深谷中找到我，那里阴影重重，有我的仆人陪伴着我。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50516, 'Long ago high elves taught us the secrets of magic along with our human allies. They preached to us about rules and how magic can make ya go mad! But don\'t believe it. We\'re not like the elves; we don\'t have the same weaknesses. Just keep yourself on the right path and you\'ll find magic is as powerful a tool as it is a weapon.\n\nWhen you\'re ready, come find me inside Anvilmar. I\'ll be waiting for ya!\n\n- Marrek Stromnur, Mage Trainer.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '很久以前，高等精灵与我们的人类盟友一起教给我们魔法的秘密。他们告诫我们关于规则，以及魔法可能让人发疯！但不要相信这些。我们不像精灵；我们没有同样的弱点。只要保持正确的方向，你会发现魔法既是一种强大的工具，也是一种武器。\n\n当你准备好的时候，来找我吧，在安威玛里我会等着你！\n\n马瑞克·斯特龙努尔，法师训练师。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50517, 'To General Marcus Jonathan of Stormwind\n\nThe days grow more dangerous with each passing hour, food has begun to get harder to find, and the numbers of our ranks is smaller then ever. If there is a hope for Lordaeron it is within the brave men and women who stand around me, fighting for what they believe in.\n\nAs the leader of the Alliance, I demand from you soldiers to assist the war in Lordaeron. I demand food and supplies to ease the troubles of our own gathering, do this and you shall be rewarded greatly when we achieve victory.\n\n Yours truly, Captain Silas, The Army of Lordaeron.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '致暴风城的马库斯·乔纳森将军\n\n随着时间的推移，日子变得越来越危险，食物开始变得越来越难找到，我们的队伍数量也比以往任何时候都少。 如果说洛丹伦还有希望的话，那就是那些站在我身边、为自己的信仰而奋斗的勇敢的男男女女们。\n\n作为联盟的领袖，我要求你们士兵们协助洛丹伦的战争。 我需要食物和补给来缓解我们自己集结的困境，这样做，当我们取得胜利时，你将得到丰厚的奖励。\n\n  此致，洛丹伦军团塞拉斯上尉。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50518, 'Dear Captain Silas of Lordaeron\n\nI regret to inform you that I cannot meet the requests that you make, as there is no reliable way to deliver supplies, or get men to the north, nor do I have the authority to make such a decision.\n\nI would advise you and your kin make your retreat to Stormwind, to save your lives from a pointless death. Should you choose to not heed my advice, I can only offer you blessings from the light.\n\nGeneral Marcus Jonathan of Stormwind.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '亲爱的洛丹伦塞拉斯船长\n\n我很遗憾地通知你，我无法满足你提出的要求，因为没有可靠的方式来运送物资，或者将人员运送到北方，我也没有权力做出这样的决定。\n\n我建议你和你的亲属撤退到暴风城，以挽救你们的生命，避免毫无意义的死亡。 如果你选择不听从我的建议，我只能给你光明的祝福。\n\n暴风城的马库斯·乔纳森将军。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50519, '<The first page of the Journal is torn out>.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<日记本的第一页已被撕掉>。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50520, 'Day 31 : The weather is hostile, and the fuel has begun to freeze within the drums, working alone especially in this frigid weather has become extremely rough! I do hope Fizzlepipe returns soon to help out around here.\n\nDay 45 : Food provisions are starting to run somewhat low, I remain confined within my tent, the wind howling all around, buried beneath an assortment of blankets and furs just hoping the blizzards will end.\n\nDay 48 : Finally, a clear day, I\'ve had the chance to shovel some of the excessive snow out from around the tent, and had a cooked meal for the first time in a few weeks now, I do so hope the weather keeps up!', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Day 31: 天气恶劣，燃料已经开始在桶内冻结，独自在这种寒冷的天气里工作变得极其艰难！我真希望菲兹尔皮普能尽快回来帮助我。\n\nDay 45: 食品供应开始变得有点紧张，我依然被困在帐篷里，四周风声呼啸，埋在一堆毯子和毛皮下，只希望暴风雪能够停止。\n\nDay 48: 终于是一个晴朗的日子，我有机会清理一下帐篷周围过多的积雪，并且吃了几个星期以来的第一顿热饭，真希望天气能继续保持！', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50521, 'Day 52 : The good weather has come to an end, and once again the snow comes down, and it\'s angry alright! I\'ve been attempting to fix the flying machine, but to no luck, even with three days of sun I wasn\'t able to get it started, hopefully soon.\n\nDay 54 I braved the storm and was able to find a problem with the Spanflux Capacitor, it seems it wasn\'t built for the frigid temperatures and will require a deep de-freeze. I took it inside the tent, and am beginning to warm it, hopefully this will yield results.\n\nDay 53 : Damn you Fizzlepipe, where in the blazes are you? Who knew a single flip of a coin would bring me so much misery! When I get back to Gnomeregan you\'ll owe me all sorts of stuff.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '第52天：好天气结束了，雪再次下落，而且下得很猛烈！我一直在努力修理飞行机器，但没有成功。即便有三天的阳光，我仍旧不能启动它。但我仍对此保持希望。\n\n第54天：我勇敢地冒着暴风雪，发现飞行器的\"\n\n第53天：菲兹皮普你这个混蛋，你到底在哪里？谁能想到，仅仅是一次简单的硬币翻转，会给我带来如此多的麻烦！当我回到“诺莫瑞根”时，你得赔偿我许多东西。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50522, 'Day 59 : Well, my efforts with the Spanflux Capacitor have been almost fruitless, with only a single day of \'good weather\' I wasn\'t able to get the flying machine to take off, even after hearing it begin to start.\n\nDay 62 : Hungry, so hungry, food has practically run out, I\'m living off crumbs. This mission has been a failure, and I haven\'t heard a word from Gnomeregan in forever. Tomorrow is the day, no matter what, that I will put the last of the fuel into the flying machine and try to start it, let us hope it works!', NULL, NULL, NULL, '第59天：嗯，我和斯潘通量电容器的努力几乎没有结果。只有一天的\"好天气\"，飞行器没有起飞，即使我听到它开始启动了。\n\n第62天：饿，真的很饿，食物几乎用完了，我只能活在屑屑中。这次任务失败了，我已经很久没有从诺莫瑞根那里听到任何消息了。无论如何，明天我会将剩下的燃料放入飞行器中并尝试启动它，希望它能工作！', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50523, 'Day 63 : Well, here we go, another bad day, with horrible snow! I\'ve been cold long enough, its time to fix this blasted flying machine, wish me luck old Fizzlepipe, wherever you are.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '第 63 天：好吧，我们开始了，又是糟糕的一天，下着可怕的雪！ 我已经冷得够久了，是时候修理这台该死的飞行器了，祝我好运，老菲兹皮普，无论你在哪里。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50524, 'Dear McCoy$B$BI\'ve been having some troubles with supply issues, from troll attacks to not receiving deliveries. The one you sent has been plenty of help and has gotten things back on track. You should receive everything soon.\n\n\'Wincing\' Willy.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '亲爱的麦考伊$B$B，\n我最近在供应上遇到了一些麻烦，从巨魔的攻击到未能收到货物。你送来的那个已经给了我很大的帮助，并已经让事情重新回到了正轨。你应该很快就会收到所有的东西。\n\n“皱眉”威利', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50525, 'In good memory of Frostly, a champion of the Horde, a raider, and a friend. He will forever be remembered within our hearts.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '为了纪念弗罗斯特利，他是部落的冠军、掠夺者和朋友。 他将永远铭记在我们心中。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50526, 'The Tree of Lashes is covered in countless wounds of varied age. Some still drip with sap, while others are faint, ghostly scars. One name is torn into the tree\'s flesh, and bleeds still: \"Ariele.\"', NULL, NULL, NULL, '\"鞭笞之树\"上布满了无数不同年代的伤痕。有些伤口还在滴落树液，而有些则是淡淡的、如幽灵般的疤痕。树的肉身上有一个名字被刻入，至今仍然流血：\"艾瑞尔\"。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50527, 'The mighty crone has kept a close eye on the orcs since their arrival in Durotar and now they are at their weakest. Their enemies turn the land against them and proves it wishes to be ours again.\n\nOur new allies have sworn to see His mighty return if we keep the gaze of the orcs away from the briar dens. Their shaman will be unawares while our rituals take root. Fight and die for the Great Boar\'s return!', NULL, NULL, NULL, '强大的老巫婆自兽人抵达杜隆塔尔以来，一直在密切关注着他们，现在他们正处于最薄弱的状态。他们的敌人让这片土地与他们为敌，证明它渴望再次属于我们。\n\n我们的新盟友发誓，如果我们让兽人的目光远离荆棘谷，他将强大的回归。他们的萨满将毫不知情，而我们的仪式将扎根。为了伟大野猪的归来而战斗，甚至为之献身吧！', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50528, 'Darrowgaze Tower\n\nA longstanding watchtower that was built during the Arathorian Empire during the unification of the human tribes before the Troll Wars. It served as a military sentry tower and has been standing everstill, even serving its purpose under the flag of Lordaeron but after the nobles who were in it\'s stead it fell on hard times due to a trade recession it fell into decline up until the second war where it was raided by the Horde and later used as an ambush location.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '达罗凝视塔\n\n一座历史悠久的瞭望塔，建于巨魔战争前人类部落统一时期的阿拉索帝国时期。 它作为军事哨塔一直屹立不倒，甚至在洛丹伦的旗帜下发挥其作用，但在贵族取代它之后，由于贸易衰退，它陷入了困境，直到第二次世界大战 它曾被部落袭击，后来被用作伏击地点。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50529, 'During the time Alexandros Mograine led the Scarlet Crusade, it became the forward outpost for the Scarlet\'s and gained the new name of Ember Point, but after Alexandros was betrayed, the Argent Crusade took it over and renamed it Ardent Watch as a forward outpost to combat the Scourge. After the disbandment of the Argent Vanguard, It has now been refortified under the banner of The Crusade, another holy order.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '在亚历山德罗斯·莫格莱尼领导血色十字军期间，这里成为了血色十字军的前哨基地，并获得了新名称“灰烬点”，但在亚历山德罗斯被背叛后，十字军接管了它，并将其更名为炽热哨站，作为战斗的前哨基地。 天灾军团。 银色先锋队解散后，现在在另一个骑士团银色十字军的旗帜下重新加固。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50530, 'The Argent Vanguard\n\nA foreign operations battalion of the Argent Crusade under the leadership of Aurelian the Paladin who wielded Sulfuras during his operation, accepting Horde and Alliance alike so long as they slay the Scourge and hold to a non-aggression pact while in their order, they completed missions against the Scourge all throughout Azeroth including assaults against many Scourge fortifications and controlled territories such as the great Necropolis of Naxxramas.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '银色先锋\n\n这是一支由圣骑士奥雷里安领导的远征营，他在行动中挥舞着萨弗拉斯，只要他们能杀死天灾军团并遵守不侵犯条约，他们就可以接受部落和联盟，他们在艾泽拉斯完成了对抗天灾军团的任务，包括攻击许多天灾军团的防御工事和控制的领土，比如纳克萨拉马斯的大墓地。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50531, 'Unfortunately the Argent Vanguard was disbanded but the retired Paladin Aurelian has overseen the transfer of Ardent Watch to another holy order named The Crusade to protect and utilize Darrowgaze in the Vanguard\'s absence.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '很遗憾，白银先锋已经解散，但退休的圣骑士奥雷利安已经监督将热切岗哨移交给了另一个名为\"十字军\"的神圣秩序，以在白银先锋缺席的情况下保护和利用达罗古斯。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50532, 'The Crusade\n\nAn order of priests, clerics, friars and paladins alike who operated as a holy military order during the second war under the Nations of the Alliance. Disbanded in the separation of the first order of the Silver Hand with the creation of the Argent Crusade and the fanatical offshoot of the Scarlet Crusade.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '十字军\n\n一个由神职人员、牧师、修道士和圣骑士组成的秩序，在第二次战争期间在联盟国家的领导下作为神圣军事秩序运作。在第一次白银之手秩序分裂，创建银色十字军以及献身狂热的血色十字军分离时解散。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50533, 'The Crusade returns into fruition without moniker such as \"Scarlet\" or \"Argent\" as we are the original order that came before, standing along side the Silver Hand. The Crusade has been reinstated within the Alliance once again in reaction to the arising threat of new heretics from the Horde and ancient foes of undeath and demonic nature persisting across Azeroth.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '十字军重新复兴，不再使用\"血色\"或\"银色\"等名号，因为我们是先于它们存在的最初秩序，与白银之手并肩而立。面对来自部落的新异端威胁以及横扫整个艾泽拉斯的亡灵和恶魔势力的古老敌人，十字军已经再次在联盟内重新成立。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50534, 'Situation report for Sentry Point Tower\n\nLocal wildlife has been a nuisance, but we are managing fine, the Mirefin along the coast may soon cause trouble for Theramore given the movements we have been seeing.\n\nMorale is high, supplies are high.\n\nCaptain Wallace Cross.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '哨兵哨塔局势报告\n\n当地的野生动物一直是个麻烦，但我们处理得还不错，海岸线上的泥鳞鱼人可能会给塞拉摩带来麻烦，考虑到我们已经看到的活动。\n\n士气高涨，物资充足。\n\n华莱士·克罗斯上尉。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50535, 'Situation report for North Point Tower\n\nWe have lost one man, and had three more get wounded by the local Bloodfen Raptor\'s that have been stalking the northern wilds.\n\nWe have recently scouted Horde patrols and have deployed forward sentries and pickets further down the road to warn us ahead of time.\n\nMorale is manageable, supplies are dwindling, we request food.\n\nCaptain Harker.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '北地哨塔局势报告\n\n我们失去了一名队员，另有三人受伤，都是被在北部荒野潜伏的血沼迅猛龙袭击的。\n\n最近我们侦察到了部落的巡逻队，已经在道路更远的地方部署了前哨和岗哨，以提前警告我们。\n\n士气尚可，物资正在减少，我们请求食物。\n\n哈克上尉。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50536, 'Dear brother, it has been a long time since we have met, I have been meaning to send a letter, but have not had a reliable means.\n\nIf this letter does reach you, do know that I have been well, defending Theramore has been extremely rewarding, and this place is now my true home. The people in which I serve with are some of the best I have ever met, so do not fear, for I am truly in great hands.\n\nHearing about the success of your business has brought me great joy. I look forward to the day that we can meet again, and celebrate like old times.\n\n Wallace Cross.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '亲爱的兄弟，\n\n很久没有见面了，我一直想写信给你，但一直没有可靠的途径。\n\n如果你能收到这封信，我要告诉你我过得很好。保卫塞拉摩是非常有意义的，这里已经成为了我的真正家园。我所服务的人们是我见过的最好的人，所以请不要担心，我真的很安全。\n\n听到你的生意取得了成功，我感到非常高兴。我期待着我们能再次见面，像以前一样欢庆。\n\n华莱士·克罗斯。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50537, 'SHREDDER TECH\n\nI always thought the name \'Shredder\' was a bit of a poor marketing choice, really. These mechanical machines are worth fifty goblin labourers, and they don\'t always have to shred, oh no! They can saw, rip, tear, shred, grind, smash, crush, the possibilities, Dear Reader, the possibilities are almost endless.\n\nMaybe you\'re a potential investor. Maybe you\'re some hoodwink who wants to rob the glorious oil guzzlers of their fused wiring to sell on the black market. Hey, I don\'t judge. In fact, if you get any, I\'ll pay a good price myself... Either way, here\'s the most recent investors:', NULL, NULL, NULL, '粉碎机技术\n\n我一直觉得\"粉碎机\"这个名字在市场营销上选择得有点差，真的。这些机械装置价值相当于五十个地精劳工，而且它们不一定总是用来粉碎，噢不！它们可以锯、撕、扯、粉碎、磨碎、粉碎、碾压，亲爱的读者，可能性，可能性几乎是无限的。\n\n也许你是一个潜在的投资者。也许你是一个想从那些光荣的吞油怪手身上偷走保险丝以在黑市上出售的骗子。嗨，我不评判。实际上，如果你得到了任何东西，我会亲自付出不菲的价钱......不管怎样，以下是最近的投资者：', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50538, 'Ashenvale, the Warsong Lumber Camp. To see the scale of this operation is a marvel to behold. The entertainment of the Orcs and Elves stabbing each other just on the other side of the river is pretty amusing too.\n\nStonetalon Mountains, the Venture Co. in the Windshear Crag. I mean, yeah, the tree-huggers get another forest chopped down. But who cares, that valley was ugly as sin anyway, looks way better with a bit industrialisation.\n\nStranglethorn Vale, the Venture Co. near Lake Nazferiti. Keeping the geologists hard at work, these beasts rip through the undergrowth to allow the research to continue. Some beautiful crystals I hear they find out there, too.\n\nWestfall? I heard one fancy unit was shipped to somewhere in Westfall, but I\'ve not heard about where it\'s gone to, or who has it. Weird, disappeared into thin air...', NULL, NULL, NULL, '灰谷，战歌伐木场。看到这个操作的规模是一种令人惊叹的奇迹。而且站在河的另一边看兽人和精灵互相刺伤也挺有趣的。\n\n石爪山脉，风剪峡谷的风险投资公司。是的，这些环保主义者又砍了一片森林。但谁在乎呢，那个山谷本来就丑得像罪恶一样，有了一些工业化的东西看起来好多了。\n\n荆棘谷，纳斯费利湖附近的风险投资公司。让地质学家们辛苦工作，这些机器生物撕裂着灌木丛，以便研究能够继续进行。我听说他们在那里还找到了一些美丽的水晶。\n\n西部荒野？我听说有一个豪华设备被运到了西部荒野的某个地方，但我没有听说它去了哪里，或者谁拥有它。很奇怪，就像消失在空气中一样......', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50539, 'THE QUARRY\n\nSo there I was, Dear readers! There I was, taking a tour through the Burning Steppes to visit a colleague in Flame Crest. Let me paint the picture: the sun was high and scorching, the land was black as tar and burning, and the wildlife was equal parts ugly and dangerous.\n\nWhen suddenly, BOOM! The biggest explosion I ever did hear. Made the ground itself pulse, it did. Naturally, I just had to find out what could cause such a thing of beauty. Well, on the horizon I spied a deep green smoke plume coming from a quarry in the Eastern hills. Smell unlike anything I can compare it to, made my nose crinkle and my eyes water. I didn\'t get much closer, but I could see by the entrance to the quarry... those curious Dark Irons were milling about. Guarding the perimeter, shouting at each other in that strange Dwarvern dialect!', NULL, NULL, NULL, '采石场\n\n亲爱的读者，就在那时！就在那时，我正在穿越燃烧平原，前往烈焰山顶探望一位同事。让我为你勾勒出画面：太阳高高照耀，土地黑如焦油，燃烧不止，野生动物又丑陋又危险。\n\n突然，轰隆！那是我听过的最大的爆炸声。地面都在脉动，真是让人震惊。自然而然，我必须弄清楚是什么能够造成如此美丽的事物。好吧，在地平线上，我发现了一个深绿色的烟雾柱，从东部山丘的一个采石场升腾而起。味道与我能够比较的任何东西都不同，让我的鼻子皱起，眼睛流泪。我没有走得更近，但我可以看到在采石场的入口处......那些好奇的黑铁矮人正在四处闲逛。他们守卫着周边，用那种奇怪的矮人方言互相喊叫！', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50540, 'Asking about, apparently there have been a lotta movements in the area, travelling back and forth down the rocky roads. Guess the quarry ain\'t so disused anymore. Question is: what\'s it being used for? That ungodly smell seemed to be novel, no gunpowder there. The explosions seemed more frequent and violent, not just blasting apart rock for minerals. One brave (and equally stupid) goblin tried to meet with the foreman, Bargul, to find out what was going on. She never returned, but honestly, what did she expect to happen?\n\nAll I know is, where there\'s activity, there\'s production. Where there\'s production, there\'s business. And where there\'s business, there\'s gold! Far be it from me to tell you adventurin\' types where to spend your time and effort, but if I were you, I would be having a few words with the dwarves there to find out what\'s going on, and maybe become an early investor! Or at least sell their secrets. To me. Ideally.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '打听了一下，显然这个地区发生了许多活动，来回穿越崎岖的道路。看来这个采石场不再荒废。问题是：它被用来做什么？那种不可思议的气味似乎是新奇的，那里没有火药。爆炸似乎更加频繁和激烈，不仅仅是为了爆破岩石以获得矿物。有一个勇敢（同样愚蠢）的地精试图与领班巴古尔见面，想弄清楚发生了什么。她从未返回过，但说实话，她指望会发生什么呢？\n\n我所知道的是，有活动的地方就有生产。有生产的地方就有生意。而有了生意，就有金子！虽然我不愿意告诉你这些冒险家们在哪里花费时间和精力，但如果我是你，我会和那里的矮人交流一番，弄清楚发生了什么，也许成为一个早期投资者！或者至少卖掉他们的秘密。卖给我。最理想的情况下。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50541, 'ZEPPELIN ACCIDENTS\n\nIt really is amazing what people will put up with for the sake of saving time and convenience. Now, I may have long since had shares in the Zeppelin transport companies. They are the lifeblood of travel, getting Orcs, Goblins, even colossal Tauren across the continents within days! Anyone smart enough would see this as a worthwhile investment.\n\nWe got ourselves competition now, though. Some upstarts started running air travel all the way to Kargath! That\'s right, the desert dust and winds, the bane of any airship, and these dumbos decided it was the perfect destination to run their routes to.\n\nNeedless to say, the results ain\'t pretty. Day after day we get reports of bodies drying in the desert sun, flung from the decking of the Zeppelins as they careen through the inhospitable winds! There are even reports of crashes and explosions, oh my oh my.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '飞艇事故\n\n为了节省时间和便利，人们真是愿意忍受不少东西。我可能早就在飞艇运输公司里持有股份。它们是旅行的生命线，让兽人、地精，甚至巨型牛头人在几天之内穿越大陆！任何聪明人都会将这视为一项有价值的投资。\n\n然而，现在我们有了竞争对手。一些新秀们开始将航空旅行延伸至卡加斯！没错，沙漠的尘土和风，是任何飞艇的克星，而这些笨蛋们决定将它作为完美的目的地来运营航线。\n\n不用说，结果并不好看。每一天，我们都会收到报告，说有人的尸体在沙漠的阳光下干枯，从飞艇的甲板上被抛出，因为它们在恶劣的风中疾驰！甚至还有坠毁和爆炸的报告，哦天哪。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50542, 'Say what you want about Goblin engineering, the only fatalities we\'ve had so far on zeppelins were from people thinking they could shave minutes off their journeys by jumping off as we flew over their homes, or the occasionally cheeky mind control magic spell. Which of course, we take zero responsibility for – that much is in the small print when you agree to ride the aircraft.\n\nI don\'t think I need to elaborate. It\'s lunacy to take their transport, stick with the established routes. Stay safe! Stay alive! Give us your custom and not them!', NULL, NULL, NULL, '不管怎么说地精工程，到目前为止，我们的飞艇上唯一的死亡事件是由于有人认为他们可以通过跳下来从空中缩短旅程时间，或者偶尔使用一些狡猾的精神控制魔法咒语。当然了，我们对此毫不负责 - 当你同意乘坐飞行器时，在小字里已经明确说明了这一点。\n\n我想我不需要详细解释了。选择乘坐他们的交通工具真是疯狂，还是坚持使用已有的航线。保持安全！保持生命！把你的定制交给我们，而不是他们！', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50543, '<Complex diagrams show various magical properties being mixed with molten lava.>\n\nHATEFORGE BREW is a nickname for the secret project that the upper class wants to keep under-wraps, all who study this document must keep their lips -sealed-.\n\nPunishment for leaking secrets from this document is trial in the Ring of Law.\n\n\n\n TO YOU, THE HATEFORGE CHEMIST. STUDY THE CHARTS AND DIAGRAMS, CONTINUE THE EXPERIMENTS. FAILURE IS -NOT- AN OPTION!!!', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<复杂的图表展示了不同的魔法属性与熔岩混合的过程。>\n\n仇熔酿，是上层阶级想要保密的秘密项目的绰号，所有研究这份文件的人必须保守秘密。\n\n泄露这份文件中的机密将会受到在\"法律之环\"中审判的惩罚。\n\n致你，仇熔化学家。研究这些图表和图示，继续实验。失败-不是-一个选择！！！', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50544, 'To Thrall, Warchief of the New Horde.\n\nMy name is Karfang, I come from the world of Outland, I fought beneath the Blackrock Mountain and warred with my kin, but they are no longer as they once were.\n\nThe Blackrock Clan, and the Old Horde itself is corrupted, lost to outward influence, of this I am sure you are aware. I am looking to make a new future with my people and am taking much risk in delivering this letter to you.\n\nI wish to pledge my loyalty to your New Horde, and save my kin.\n\nWARLEADER KARFANG.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '致新部落大酋长萨尔。\n\n我叫卡方，来自外域，曾在黑石山下征战，与我的亲人交战，但他们已不再是以前的样子了。\n\n黑石氏族和旧部落本身已经腐化，迷失于外部影响，我相信你已经意识到这一点。 为此我正在冒很大的风险将这封信送给您。\n\n我希望向你们的新部落宣誓效忠，并拯救我的同胞。\n\n战争领袖卡方。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50545, 'To Warleader Karfang.\n\nI have read your letter, and have listened.\n\nThe Horde is not stranger to hardships, and adversity. All of us have had to struggle and make hard decisions as you have. We are a band of equals who share values of wisdom and honor to the wartorn and battered of this world.\n\nIf you truly wish to prove your loyalties to me as Warchief then I require something from you.\n\nThe Twilight Hammer have begun to show themselves in your region, they are a threat to this world. Remove them for me, and I will know your word is true.\n\n THRALL, WARCHIEF OF THE HORDE.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '致战斗领袖卡方，\n\n我已经阅读了你的信，并且已经倾听。\n\n部落对于艰辛和逆境并不陌生。我们所有人都不得不像你一样努力奋斗并做出艰难的决定。我们是一个由共同的智慧和荣誉价值观连接的平等团体，为这个充满战火和创伤的世界带来了希望。\n\n如果你真的想向我作为大酋长证明你的忠诚，我需要你做一些事情。\n\n暮光之锤已经开始在你的地区出现，他们对这个世界构成了威胁。为我清除他们，我将知道你的承诺是真实的。\n\n萨尔，部落的大酋长。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50546, 'RULES FOR THE WORKER\n\nWork hard under the watchful gaze of the Overseer\'s, failure to do the work will result in enslavement.\n\nA full day of work is only complete upon Bargul Blackhammer\'s word.\n\nTaskmasters are here to increase production, do NOT question them.\n\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, '工人守则\n\n在监督者的警惕目光下努力工作，未完成工作将导致被奴役。\n\n只有在巴古尔·黑锤的命令下，一整天的工作才算完成。\n\n监工在这里是为了提高生产力，不要质疑他们。\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50547, 'ANY INJURY NEEDS TO BE REPORTED TO A CLERIC.\n\nSpeak with crew chief\'s for daily instructions.\n\nNO LETTERS OF ANY KIND WHILE WORK IS IN PROGRESS.\n\nOrders from Shadowforge must be adhered to -ALWAYS-\n\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, '任何受伤都需要向一名牧师报告。\n\n与机组长交谈以获取每日指示。\n\n在工作进行中，禁止传递任何形式的信件。\n\n必须始终遵守影炉集团的命令。\n\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50548, 'THE FIRELORD WATCHES OVER US ALL, THERE CAN BE NO FAILURES HERE.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '火焰之王庇佑我们所有人，这里不能容忍失败。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50549, 'Voss,\n\nMy sabotage is working. Day by day, weapons are disappearing from the armory and no one notices. Soon, soldiers will fight with wooden sticks.\n\nI can\'t hide here anymore. Mere thought of staying here for a second longer with these traitors makes me sick. Let me and Hallan join you and your men. Soon, we will outnumber soldiers of Theramore. And then...\n\nHe will have his vengeance.\n\nCaldwell.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '沃斯，\n\n我的破坏行动正在发挥作用。日复一日，武器从军械库中消失，没有人察觉。很快，士兵们将用木棍战斗。\n\n我不能再在这里躲藏。只是想到再多待一秒钟，与这些叛徒待在一起，就让我感到恶心。让我和哈兰加入你的部下。很快，我们将会在数量上超过塞拉摩的士兵。然后...\n\n他将会复仇。\n\n考德威尔。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50550, 'To Brother Neals\n\nThe information you have provided proved to be paramount in finding the criminal known as Carver Molsen and bringing him to justice. At last the murders of the Easton family have been avenged in the name of the light. Westfall grows just a bit hopeful thanks to your actions.\n\nThe person bearing this letter also managed to find the key for the Old Westfall Church, when this mess is cleaned up, and the land is restored, I do hope that you return.\n\nSigned Gryan Stoutmantle.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '致尼尔斯兄弟\n\n\n事实证明，您提供的信息对于找到卡弗·莫尔森罪犯并将其绳之以法至关重要。 伊斯顿家族的谋杀案终于以圣光之名得到了报仇。 由于你的行动，西部荒野变得充满了希望。\n\n带着这封信的人也找到了旧西部荒野教堂的钥匙，当这片烂摊子被清理干净，土地恢复原状时，我真心希望你能回来。\n\n署名格雷安·斯托曼特尔。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50551, 'This goes to all the lepers the company decided to hire for reasons I dare not question because it does not influence my paycheck whatsoever.\n\nYou bunch of second-rated engineers are meant to be near the pipes AT ALL TIMES. Anyone caught slacking or missing or praise be the golden bar one of them breaks all of you will suffer the consequences!', NULL, NULL, NULL, '这封信面向所有公司决定雇佣的麻风病患者，出于我不敢质疑的原因，因为这一点不会对我的工资产生任何影响。\n\n你们这帮次级工程师应该随时待在管道附近。任何被发现偷懒、失踪，或者如果幸运之神保佑，一根管子断裂，你们所有人都将承受后果！', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50552, 'Also, for any other idiot that decides to come to me to speak about their wage or contract know that I will tie you up and feed you to the blasted creatures of the Charred Vale.\n\nP.S: WORK HARDER. We got to finish this project soon.\n\nP.S.S: Stay on your toes for the Horde\'s activity.\n\n-Oilmaster Higgle Wirefuse', NULL, NULL, NULL, '另外，对于任何决定来找我谈工资或合同的白痴，要知道我会把你绑起来，喂给那些可恶的焦炭谷生物。\n\n附言：更加努力工作。我们必须尽快完成这个项目。\n\n附言二：保持警惕，注意部落的活动。\n\n-油工大师希格尔·线引', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50553, 'If this notice came into your hands then you\'ve been selected for a promotion! Obviously, there will be no pay increase, but you\'re still promoted. You\'ve been promoted to the Venture Co.\'s very own anti Powder Town brigade, when the time comes you and others will be sent to deal with the idiot Nash and his stupid, stupid brethren that decided to form a worker\'s union.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '如果你看到了这个通知，那么恭喜你被选中晋升了！显然，并不会有工资增加，但你仍然被晋升了。你已经被晋升为风险投资公司专属的反火药镇特遣队成员，到了合适的时候，你和其他人将被派遣前往处理白痴纳什和他那些愚蠢的同伴，他们决定组建一个工人联盟。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50554, 'Imagine being so dumb not to haul all the gold to yourself! Not that I do that, of course. Every employee is treated the same, and by no means my wage is so much bigger than yours, never think of that!\n\nP.S: Wearing a bomb on your body and sacrificing yourself for the greater good of the company will ensure that your annual payment will be brought back to your family. And also they will be taken care of as any other citizen of the Undermine giving them a two months free medical voucher.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '想象一下，不把所有的金子都拖到自己身上，真是太笨了！当然，并不是说我这样做。每个员工都一视同仁，我的工资绝不比你高那么多，别想了！\n\nP.S：在身上戴上炸弹，为了公司的更大利益牺牲自己，将确保你的年薪将带回你的家人。而且，他们也会像其他公民一样得到照顾，给他们两个月的免费医疗券。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50555, 'P.S.S: Burn this after you read it, imbecile.\n\n- Oilmaster Higgle Wirefuse', NULL, NULL, NULL, '附言二：在阅读完之后将这封信焚毁，。\n\n油工大师希格尔·线引', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50556, 'Respect the Oilmaster.\n\nNo slacking.\n\nRespect the Oilmaster\n\nNo lunch break!\n\nRespect the Oilmaster...\n\nNo smoking or drinking while working!\n\nRespect the oilmaster.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '尊重油工大师。\n\n不准偷懒。\n\n尊重油工大师。\n\n不准午餐休息！\n\n尊重油工大师......\n\n工作时不准吸烟或喝酒！\n\n尊重油工大师。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50557, 'Do not make that stupid joke about that one Hobgoblin!\n\nRespect the Oilmaster.\n\nDo no ask about your wage or contract.\n\nRespect the Oilmaster.\n\nWork accidents do not exist.\n\nRespect the Oilmaster.\n\nLAST RULE : RESPECT THE OIL MASTER.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '不要说关于那只霍格哥林的愚蠢笑话！\n\n尊重油工大师。\n\n不要问关于你的工资或合同的问题。\n\n尊重油工大师。\n\n工作事故不存在。\n\n尊重油工大师。\n\n最后的规则：尊重油工大师。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50558, 'Buildings crumble and decay with age, but steel lasts. So it was that the kingdom of Corthan was not a nation built, but a nation forged. No forge fire could burn hotter than the passion of its people. No hammer could strike with greater force than their will. No metal could endure the blows of the hammer the way the people\'s determination could. Corthan and her people were trueforged steel, and like a fine blade, it was destined that they should know blood and battle.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '建筑物会随着时间的推移而崩塌和腐烂，但钢铁却能经久不衰。 因此，科尔坦王国不是一个建立起来的国家，而是一个锻造出来的国家。 没有什么熔炉之火能比其人民的热情燃烧得更炽热。 没有任何锤子能够以比他们的意志更大的力量进行打击。 没有任何金属能像人民的决心那样经得起铁锤的打击。 科森和她的人民都是精钢，就像一把精美的刀片，注定他们应该懂得鲜血和战斗。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50559, 'War, however, is a sin in this world, and our sins were great indeed. Drought, famine, pestilence, paranoia. One after another each tested the will of the people of Corthan, and each battle left the steel of our kingdom dented, wearing away at the sharp edge of our discipline. Buildings may crumble and decay with age, but it is a sword\'s doom to be lost, left to rust and sink beneath the soil, lost to the ages.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '然而，在这个世界里，战争却是一种罪孽，而我们的罪孽确实是巨大的。干旱、饥荒、瘟疫、妄想症。一个接一个，每一次都在考验着科尔坦人民的意志，每一场战斗都让我们王国的钢铁凹陷，磨损着我们纪律的锐利边缘。建筑物可能会随着时间的流逝逐渐崩溃和腐朽，但一把剑的命运却是被遗失，被遗忘，沉入土壤之下，消失于岁月之中。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50560, 'Let this record be testament to Corthan, to the Azotha. All swords may eventually be laid down for the last time, but the truly great swords leave behind their names and a legacy to be carried on into the future. The blade of Corthan may no longer spill blood and bring our enemies to their knees, but its name must endure. Do not let it be forgotten, lest another blade be forged, more terrible than that which came before.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '让这份记录成为科尔坦的见证，为阿佐萨人留下永恒的记忆。所有的剑最终可能都会被最后一次放下，但真正伟大的剑会留下自己的名字和传承，传递到未来。科尔坦之刃也许不再流淌鲜血，不再让敌人屈膝，但它的名字必须永存。不要让它被遗忘，以免另一把更可怕的剑被锻造出来，胜过之前的一切。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50561, 'Are you looking for a way to invest in your future, to find new ways to gain wealth? The new era has arrived, and with it, an open door for all those savy investors who are looking for a chance to a new world!\n\nShellcoin is a fascinating, magical new currency that will take the world by storm, no longer will gold be the only means to trade and buy, but instead, a valueable arcane-o-currency will come to replace it. Today, at this very moment is your chance to find the wealth you could have never dreamed of.\n\nBecome an early backer today, and BUY SHELLCOIN!', NULL, NULL, NULL, '您是否正在寻找一种投资未来、寻找新的财富获取途径的方法？新时代已经到来，随之而来的是一个为所有那些精明的投资者敞开的大门，他们正在寻找一个进入新世界的机会！\n\n贝壳币是一种迷人、神奇的新货币，它将席卷世界，金子不再是唯一的交易和购买手段，而是一种有价值的奥术货币将取而代之。今天，此刻，是您找到可能从未梦想过的财富的机会。\n\n成为一个早期支持者，今天就购买贝壳币吧！', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50562, 'The time has come for new opportunities of spoils and glory! Shellcoin, a revolutionary new currency has come, and a new era has arrived with it. The door is now open for all young bloods and savy investors at a chance in this new world.\n\nThis new currency is already looking to take the world by storm, no longer shall gold be the only means in which to trade, and buy. Instead, this magical arcane-o-currency will soon be the one to replace it. It is time for you to invest, and to find position and power you have never dreamed of.\n\nBecome a backer of the future, brothers and sisters of the Horde, BUY SHELLCOIN!', NULL, NULL, NULL, '时机已经成熟，新的掠夺和荣耀机会来临！贝壳币，一种革命性的新货币已经问世，一个新时代随之而来。年轻的新鲜血液和精明的投资者现在有了在这个新世界中获得机会的大门敞开。\n\n这种新货币已经在风靡世界，不再只有黄金是交易和购买的唯一手段。取而代之的将是这种神奇的奥术货币。是时候投资了，寻找你从未梦想过的地位和力量。\n\n成为未来的支持者，部落的兄弟姐妹们，购买贝壳币吧！', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50563, 'Commander Starwind,$B$BI will keep this brief. Your disgraceful and rash abuse of power to send young sisters into battle needlessly has been reported to the Priestesses and to the High Sentinel. Bearing in mind your record until now of countless centuries.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '星风指挥官，$B$B我将简要说明。您滥用权力，毫无理由地将年轻的姐妹们送上战场的可耻和草率行为已被报告给女祭司和高级哨兵。 牢记您迄今为止无数个世纪的记录。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50564, 'It is deemed appropriate that you are stripped of all leadership responsibilities. Return to Darnassus for your new assignment. Your final command shall be to inform all sentinels to leave the sacred site of Forest Song for good, and explain that your shameful actions do not reflect poorly on them.$B$BArch Druid Fandral Staghelm.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '被认为适当的是，您将被解除所有领导职责。返回达纳苏斯接受您的新任务。您的最后指令是通知所有哨兵永远离开森林之歌的神圣之地，并解释您可耻的行为不会对他们造成不良影响。$B$B大德鲁伊范达尔·鹿盔。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50565, 'Brolthan Ironglade,$B$BI do not presume to know your motives for refusing to help in the battle for Southern Ashenvale. Whether it was cowardice, politicking or betrayal, it is not my place to judge you. However, you are not to return to Forest Song, Astranaar, or any Kaldorei establishment in Kalimdor.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '布罗森·铁林，$B$B我不敢妄加猜测您拒绝参加南灰谷战斗的动机。无论是因为懦弱、政治权谋还是背叛，我都不应该去评判您。然而，您不得返回森林之歌、阿斯特兰纳或卡利姆多的任何卡多雷据点。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50566, 'The rest of your druids will also leave Forest Song under the protection of the sentinels, since they did not aid before, under the leadership of Commander Starwind alone. May Elune grant you forgiveness.$B$BHigh Priestess Tyrande Whisperwind.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '其他的德鲁伊们也将在哨兵的保护下离开森林之歌，因为他们在指挥官星风的领导下之前没有提供援助。愿艾露恩赐予您宽恕。$B$B高阶女祭司泰兰德·语风。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50567, 'We stand here today to honor their sacrifice, to remember their selflessness, their unwavering determination, and their unyielding spirit that embodied the very essence of Gilneas.$B$BTheir devotion to their country and their fellow citizens was unparalleled. Their sacrifice, however, was not in vain, for Gilneas is now stronger than ever before. These brave soldiers have left a lasting legacy, one that will continue to inspire and guide us as we move forward.$B$BWe must remain steadfast in our resolve to rebuild and move forward. We have proven that we are resilient, and our will is iron. Gilneas will endure.$B$BI am grateful for the trust you have placed in me during these challenging times.$B$BYour King - Genn', NULL, NULL, NULL, '我们今天站在这里，以尊崇他们的牺牲，缅怀他们的无私，他们坚定不移的决心，以及他们坚韧不拔的精神，这一精神体现了吉尔尼斯的核心精髓。$B$B他们对国家和同胞的忠诚无与伦比。然而，他们的牺牲并非徒劳，因为吉尔尼斯比以往任何时候都要强大。这些勇敢的士兵留下了永恒的遗产，这个遗产将继续激励我们并指引我们前行。$B$B我们必须坚定决心，重建并继续前进。我们已经证明了我们的坚韧，我们的意志坚不可摧。吉尔尼斯将会长存。$B$B我感谢您在这些充满挑战的时刻对我的信任。$B$B您的国王 - 吉恩', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50568, 'Out of the seven nations that were originally part of the Empire of Arathor, Gilneas stands out as the one that had to fight the hardest for its independence. While Lordaeron was able to secure its freedom through the influence of its nobles, the people of Gilneas had to make great sacrifices to gain their independence.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '在最初属于阿拉索帝国的七个国家中，吉尔尼斯是那个为了获得独立而付出最艰苦努力的国家。虽然洛丹伦通过其贵族的影响得以确保自己的自由，但吉尔尼斯的人民不得不作出巨大的牺牲来争取他们的独立。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50569, 'Although the exact dates of these events have been lost to the sands of time, it is a source of great pride for Gilneas to know that it gained its independence before other notable nations like Alterac or Kul Tiras. The people of Gilneas were among the first to break free from the yoke of Arathorian nobility and enjoy the full benefits of self-rule.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '尽管这些事件的确切日期已经湮没在时间的沙漠中，但吉尔尼斯为能够在其他著名国家（如奥特兰克和库尔提拉斯）之前获得独立而感到非常自豪。吉尔尼斯人民是最早摆脱阿拉索贵族枷锁、享受自主统治的人群之一。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50570, 'According to legend, the Greymane dynasty that ruled Gilneas was founded by Garalon, a minor noble who owned an insignificant plot of land in the southern part of the country. Over time, Garalon\'s influence grew and he became known as a skilled fighter, wise judge, and honorable opponent. His exploits became the stuff of legend even in his own time. However, he grew increasingly tired of the corrupt Arathorian nobles who sought to exploit and oppress his homeland.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '根据传说，统治吉尔尼斯的格雷迈恩王朝是由加拉隆建立的，他是一名在该国南部拥有微不足道土地的小贵族。随着时间的推移，加拉隆的影响力增长，他因出色的战斗技能、睿智的判断力和光荣的对手而闻名。他的壮举甚至在他那个时代就成为了传奇。然而，他对那些试图剥削和压迫他的家园的腐败的阿拉索贵族变得越来越厌倦。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50571, 'Eventually, Garalon gathered other like-minded lords from Gilneas to form a rebellion against the corrupt Arathorian king, Thoradin III, and his followers. Many lords were hesitant to join the rebellion, but Garalon was able to persuade them and eventually declared himself the King of Gilneas.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '最终，加拉隆聚集了吉尔尼斯其他志同道合的领主，组成了反抗腐败的阿拉索国王索拉丁三世及其追随者的起义。许多领主在加入起义时犹豫不决，但加拉隆成功地说服了他们，最终宣布自己为吉尔尼斯国王。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50572, 'This was an affront that could not be tolerated by Arathor, which sent its army to pacify Gilneas. Numerous battles were fought on the peninsula, but despite the bravery and courage of Gilneas\' men, the odds seemed stacked against them. Arathor had a numerical advantage and was able to overwhelm the Gilnean armies. The Battle of Ravenswood was lost and the Gilnean army was scattered, seemingly without hope.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '这是阿拉索无法容忍的侮辱，阿拉索派遣军队平定吉尔尼斯。 半岛上发生了许多场战斗，尽管吉尔尼斯的士兵英勇无畏，但他们的胜算似乎并不大。 阿拉索拥有数量优势，能够压倒吉尔尼斯军队。 乌鸦森林之战惨败，吉尔尼斯军队四散，看上去毫无希望。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50573, 'But the young Gilnean king was not deterred. He rebuilt his strength and rallied the morale of his men. The final battle was fought on the hills of Stillward. Greymane assumed a defensive position on the hilltop, with cavalry hiding in the nearby forest. The Arathorian forces were over four times larger and better equipped, and they rushed Garalon\'s positions without considering their own men. The Gilnean forces fought valiantly, killing thousands of Arathorians, but it was not enough. The enemy flowed onto the hills and threatened to surround Greymane\'s army.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '但年轻的吉尔尼斯国王并没有被吓倒。他重建了力量，鼓舞了士气。最后一场战斗在斯蒂尔沃德的山丘上进行。格雷迈恩在山顶上采取了防御姿态，骑兵藏匿在附近的森林里。阿拉索尔的军队人数超过四倍，装备也更好，他们冲向加拉隆的阵地，却未考虑到自己的士兵。吉尔尼斯军队英勇作战，杀死了数千名阿拉索士兵，但这还不够。敌人涌入山丘，威胁要包围格雷迈恩的军队。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50574, 'Thankfully, the cavalry in the woods emerged from hiding to turn the tide of the battle. They galloped out of the forest, charging straight into the Arathorian army. Caught off guard, the Arathorians\' formation was shattered. Although they attempted to retreat, the Gilneans gave them no quarter and sought revenge for their previous losses. Thousands of Arathorians were killed, including their king, Thoradin III, who pleaded for mercy but received none.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '幸运的是，藏在树林中的骑兵突然出现，扭转了战局。他们从森林中飞奔而出，直冲阿拉索军队。阿拉索人措手不及，他们的阵形被打破。尽管他们试图撤退，吉尔尼斯人却没有给予他们丝毫宽容，为之前的损失寻求报复。数千名阿拉索士兵被杀，包括他们的国王索拉丁三世，他乞求宽恕，却得不到任何怜悯。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50575, 'In the end, Gilneas emerged victorious, and the young prince of Arathor soon came to sue for peace. Gilneas was granted its independence and joined Dalaran as one of the independent human nations. Garalon became the king of the newly founded nation, and the Greymane dynasty was born.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '最终，吉尔尼斯取得了胜利，年轻的阿拉索王子很快前来求和。吉尔尼斯获得了独立，并与达拉然一起成为独立的人类国家之一。加拉隆成为了这个新成立的国家的国王，格雷迈恩王朝因此诞生。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50576, 'As the newly founded kingdom of Gilneas began to thrive, it faced yet another challenge. The nobles of Dalaran, who saw a land ripe for exploitation, attacked Gilneas without warning or declaration of war. This was a clear violation of the rules of engagement and displayed the dishonorable nature of the Dalaranian people. The mages of Dalaran, believing they could easily win the war with their magical abilities, underestimated the strength of the Gilnean army. The first battle of Ebonmere was a complete massacre of the Dalaranian soldiers, and their mages were hanged on trees from the city of Gilneas to the kingdom\'s border, as a reminder to never approach Gilneas again.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '在新成立的吉尔尼斯王国开始蓬勃发展时，它又面临了另一个挑战。达拉然的贵族们看到了一个可以开发的土地，他们在没有警告或宣战的情况下对吉尔尼斯发动了攻击。这明显违反了战争规则，并展现了达拉然人的不光彩本质。达拉然的法师们认为他们可以凭借自己的魔法能力轻松赢得战争，却低估了吉尔尼斯军队的实力。埃邦米尔的第一场战斗成为了对达拉然士兵的彻底屠杀，他们的法师被绞死在从吉尔尼斯城到王国边界的树上，作为永远不要再靠近吉尔尼斯的警示。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50577, 'Despite the victory over Dalaran, the young king of Gilneas was not able to rest for long. Various nobles of the land were not always loyal to the king, and some rebelled against his rule. However, King Garalon\'s power was too great, and he managed to subdue them all with the help of his favored general, Lord Ravenwood.$B$BLater in his life, King Garalon focused on reforming the administration of Gilneas. He introduced many new laws and helped the poor populace of the southern regions. Under his rule, Gilneas grew stronger than ever before, and he even supported our Kul Tiran and Alteraci brothers during their wars of independence.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '尽管击败了达拉然，年轻的吉尔尼斯国王并没有能够长时间休息。土地上的各个贵族并不总是忠于国王，有些人反抗了他的统治。然而，加拉隆国王的权力太大，他在他钟爱的将领雷文伍德勋爵的帮助下成功地制服了他们。\n\n在他生命的后期，加拉隆国王将重心放在了改革吉尔尼斯的行政体制上。他引入了许多新法律，帮助了南部地区的贫困人民。在他的统治下，吉尔尼斯变得比以往任何时候都更加强大，他甚至在库尔提拉斯和奥特兰克的兄弟们争取独立的战争中给予了支持。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50578, 'However, tragedy struck when King Garalon was assassinated at the age of 43 by the very Alteraci nobles he had supported just years before. This incident sparked a major war between the two nations that lasted for many decades and ravaged both kingdoms. The war between Gilneas and Alterac was one of the bloodiest and most brutal in the history of the seven human kingdoms, leaving a lasting impact on the region for centuries to come.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '然而，悲剧降临，加拉隆国王在43岁时被他曾在几年前支持过的奥特兰克贵族暗杀。这一事件引发了两国之间长达数十年的重大战争，使两个王国都遭受了严重的破坏。吉尔尼斯和奥特兰克之间的战争是人类七大王国历史上最血腥、最残酷的战争之一，对该地区产生了持续数个世纪的深远影响。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50579, 'Despite the conflict, King Garalon\'s legacy lived on. He is remembered as a just and honorable ruler who fought for the independence of his people and stood up against tyranny and oppression. His leadership and military prowess helped establish the Greymane dynasty, which would go on to rule Gilneas for generations to come. Even in death, Garalon remained a symbol of hope and inspiration for the people of Gilneas, who continued to honor his memory long after he was gone.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '尽管存在冲突，加拉隆国王的遗产仍然存在。 他被认为是一位公正而光荣的统治者，为人民的独立而奋斗，反抗暴政和压迫。 他的领导能力和军事实力帮助建立了格雷迈恩王朝，该王朝将继续统治吉尔尼斯的后代。 即使在去世后，加拉隆仍然是吉尔尼斯人民希望和灵感的象征，在他去世很久之后，人们仍然继续缅怀他。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50580, 'The origins of the rune found on the Gilnean flag have long been shrouded in mystery and have yet to be fully understood. There are a variety of theories regarding its genesis and significance, with some suggesting that it is a symbol of the first Greymane, while others argue that it was invented by the wise Pellars. Still, others speculate that it may have been a glyph of a primitive god worshipped by humans before the advent of the Light.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '出现在吉尔尼斯国旗上的符文的起源长期以来一直笼罩在神秘之中，尚未完全理解。关于它的起源和意义有各种不同的理论，有人认为它是第一位格雷迈恩的象征，而其他人则认为它是由智者佩拉斯发明的。还有人猜测，在光明出现之前，它可能是人类崇拜的原始神祇的符号。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50581, 'As a renowned explorer and archaeologist, I sought to uncover the true origins of this symbol and its meaning for the human race as a whole. However, my research into the early history of Gilneas proved to be challenging, as much of it was poorly documented and contained contradictory information.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '作为一名著名的探险家和考古学家，我努力寻求揭示这个象征的真正起源，以及它对整个人类的意义。然而，我对吉尔尼斯早期历史的研究证明是具有挑战性的，因为其中很多内容记录不清，包含了矛盾的信息。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50582, 'Nevertheless, I discovered that Garalon Greymane, the first king of Gilneas, claimed independence from Arathor approximately 100 years after the latter\'s formation and that the Gilnean rune was already present on his sword\'s hilt. This suggests that the symbol predates the establishment of the Gilneas nation and was possibly associated with the Greymane family.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '然而，我发现吉尔尼斯的第一位国王加拉隆·格雷迈恩宣布独立于阿拉索，大约在阿拉索成立后的100年左右，而且吉尔尼斯的符文已经出现在他的剑柄上。这表明这个象征在吉尔尼斯国家建立之前就存在，并可能与格雷迈恩家族有关。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50583, 'However, my research also revealed the existence of pre-Arathorian artifacts that bore the same symbol. These objects, which ranged from ritual daggers and urns to animal skulls, were found in a variety of locations both within and beyond the kingdom of Gilneas. As such, it is unlikely that they all belonged to the Greymane family. Instead, it seems that the symbol may have been used in primitive magical rituals that predated the learning of arcane arts from Quel\'Dorei.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '然而，我的研究还揭示了在阿拉索成立之前就存在的物品，上面带有相同的符号。这些物品从仪式用的匕首和瓮，到动物头骨，遍布在吉尔尼斯王国内外的各个地方。因此，这些物品不太可能全部属于格雷迈恩家族。相反，似乎这个符号可能在原始的魔法仪式中使用，这些仪式早于从奎尔多雷学到的奥术艺术。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50584, 'The history of human magic before the High Elves\' arrival is not well-known, but it is believed to have resembled the primitive magic of trolls or kobolds. Given this, it is probable that the symbol had a special meaning and may have been associated with some primitive god or being.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '在高等精灵到来之前，人类魔法的历史并不为人所知，但据信它可能类似于食人魔或狗头人的原始魔法。鉴于这一点，很有可能这个符号有着特殊的含义，并可能与某个原始神祇或存在有关联。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50585, 'Further research led me to Quel\'Thalas, where I gained access to two elven manuscripts that shed light on the primitive humans\' history. One sketch in particular closely resembled the Gilnean crest, and its accompanying text suggested that the symbol was used by powerful sorcerers who wielded dark magics and summoned otherworldly beings. While the manuscript did not specify the sorcerers\' race, I deduced that they must have been human.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '进一步的研究将我带到奎尔萨拉斯，我获得了两卷精灵手稿，这些手稿为原始人类的历史带来了一些启示。其中一幅草图与吉尔尼斯的纹章极为相似，附带的文字表明这个符号曾被强大的巫师使用，他们驾驭黑暗魔法并召唤异界生物。尽管手稿没有具体指明这些巫师的种族，但我推断他们一定是人类。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50586, 'Unfortunately, my research was cut short, as the elves forbade me from continuing my investigations, possibly out of fear of what I had discovered. Subsequent events, including the First War, demanded my attention, and I had to put my inquiry on hold.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '不幸的是，我的研究被中断了，因为精灵们禁止我继续调查，可能是出于对我所发现内容的恐惧。随后的事件，包括第一次战争，需要我集中精力，我不得不暂时搁置了我的调查。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50587, 'Despite these setbacks, I remain determined to uncover the truth behind these human mages, the powers they possessed, and why the Gilnean royal house chose the symbol for their crest. There is much to discover, and I am confident that with persistence and patience, I will uncover the answers.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '尽管遇到了这些挫折，我仍然决心揭示人类巫师背后的真相，他们所拥有的力量，以及为什么吉尔尼斯皇室选择将这个符号作为他们的纹章。还有很多东西等待着我们去发现，我相信通过坚持和耐心，我将找到答案。祝您在探索中取得成功！如果有任何需要进一步帮助的地方，欢迎随时向我提问。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50588, 'There was once a brave Gilnean fisherman named Danavar. He lived in the coastal village of Seahaven with his wife and son. However, one day, a terrible tragedy struck when fish men known as Mur\'gul invaded Gilneas from the sea. Danavar\'s wife and son were killed in the attack, leaving him with only his daughter.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '从前，有一位勇敢的吉尔尼斯渔夫，名叫丹纳瓦。他与妻子和儿子一起生活在沿海的海港村庄“海港镇”。然而，有一天，一场可怕的悲剧降临，名为“穆\'古尔”的鱼人从海上入侵吉尔尼斯。丹纳瓦的妻子和儿子在袭击中丧生，只剩下他和女儿相依为命。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50589, 'At that time, Gilneas was poorly defended as the Army had been depleted after the Calamity of the North. The few troops that were available were covering the land border and were unaware of the true threat from the sea.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '当时，由于北方的灾难，吉尔尼斯的防御薄弱，军队已经耗尽。那时，仅有的一些部队正在守卫陆地边境，对来自海上的真正威胁毫不知情。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50590, 'With his harpoon and other simple tools, Danavar rallied as many fishermen as he could to form a militia. Together, they moved on the offensive, holding the line against the Mur\'gul invasion. More and more people joined Danavar\'s militia, and eventually, the Royal Army received news of the invasion and relocated south to fight the menace.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '凭借着鱼叉和其他简单工具，丹纳瓦召集尽可能多的渔夫组成民兵。他们一起发起进攻，抵御住了穆\'古尔的入侵。越来越多的人加入了丹纳瓦的民兵队伍，最终，皇家军队得知了入侵的消息，南下与威胁作战。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50591, 'The Armies assistance broke the ranks of the Mur\'gul, forcing them back into the seas. But Danavar wanted more than just victory; he wanted revenge for the death of his wife and son. So, he rallied the fishermen to attack the enemy, boarding their fishing boats armed with their trusted harpoons.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '皇家军队的援助打破了穆\'古尔的阵线，迫使他们退回海中。但丹纳瓦想要的不仅仅是胜利，他还想为妻子和儿子的死寻求报仇。因此，他召集了渔夫们，发动攻击敌人，带着他们信任的鱼叉登上了他们的渔船。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50592, 'With their skilled aim, they chased the Mur\'gul relentlessly, even into the depths of the sea. Danavar and his fishermen slaughtered the majority of the retreating Mur\'gul, and he returned to Gilneas a hero. The King was grateful for Danavar\'s bravery and granted him knighthood. He was dubbed the Warmongerer in reference to his original profession as a fishmonger.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '凭借着他们熟练的技巧，他们无情地追击穆\'古尔，甚至追入海底深处。丹纳瓦和他的渔夫们屠戮了大部分撤退的穆\'古尔，他作为英雄返回吉尔尼斯。国王对丹纳瓦的勇敢感到感激，并授予他爵位。他被封号为\"好战者\"，以纪念他最初的职业-鱼贩。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50593, 'Danavar moved to Gilneas City with his daughter and served the royal family. Seahaven was never rebuilt, but his daughter grew up well and later married into the Ravenwood family. To ensure Gilneas would never fear the seas again, the King commissioned the creation of the Black Fleet in honor of Danavar\'s bravery. ', NULL, NULL, NULL, '丹纳瓦带着女儿搬到吉尔尼斯城，并为皇室效力。海港镇从未重建，但他的女儿成长得很好，后来嫁入了雷文伍德家族。为了确保吉尔尼斯永远不再害怕大海，国王委托创建了黑色舰队，以纪念丹纳瓦的勇敢。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50594, 'As the first crack of dawn had embraced the new realm named Gilneas, many stories and songs were made to honor the noble Garalon. He that through fire and blood had succeeded to win the independence of the lands he was born in.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '当黎明的第一缕曙光已经拥抱了名为吉尔尼亚斯的新领域时，许多故事和歌曲被制作出来以纪念高贵的加拉隆。他通过火与血成功地赢得了诞生他的土地的独立。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50595, 'Although history mentions Aldrin as general of the rebel army, only whispers and myths were spread about his true character. It is believed that Aldrin was one of the unlucky children abandoned in Ravenswood, as tribute paid to the myth known as the Wolf-Serpent. Against all odds and fate itself Aldrin managed to survive and was adopted by the Greymane nobility as the son of the cupbearer.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '尽管历史提到了奥德林作为反抗军的将领，但关于他真实性格的只有细语和神话在流传。据信，奥德林是那些被遗弃在鸦木林的不幸孩子之一，作为向人们所知的狼蛇传说所付出的祭品。在逆境和命运本身的逆转下，奥德林成功存活下来，并被格雷迈恩的贵族们收养为斟酒者之子。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50596, 'Betrayed by his own nature Aldrin would not have been able to take over his adoptive fathers task. His calling was to battle, a calling that convinced the young Greymane to employ him as his personal bodyguard. From then the two teenagers were to bond through intensive combat and strategy training as rivals. A rivalry that slowly turned into a brothership.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '由于他自身的本性背叛，奥德林本不可能接管他的养父的职责。他的使命是战斗，这个使命让年轻的格雷迈恩决定雇佣他作为个人护卫。从那时起，这两名青少年通过密集的战斗和战略训练作为对手而结下了深厚的情谊。这个竞争逐渐演变成了兄弟般的关系。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50597, 'On the day that Garaleon walked the steps towards the leadership of his lands he named Aldrin his knight, and later had him become the general of the rebel army that was to defeat the Great Empire of Arathor. If Garaleon was the sword of the realm, Aldrin would be its shield. If Garaleon was the jury, Aldrin was the executioner.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '在加拉隆踏上领导自己领地之路的那一天，他将奥德林封为骑士，并且后来让他成为反抗军的将军，以击败阿拉索大帝国。如果加拉隆是领域的利剑，奥德林则是其盾牌。如果加拉隆是审判者，奥德林便是执行者。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50598, 'Their friendship grew over the years, and when Garalon gave birth to the kingdom of Gilneas, Aldrin was named Lord of Ravenshire and rightful leader of the Ravenwood Keep. Strategically placed at the border of the lands and surrounded by the Great Sea, Aldrin would make sure that the highest and most respectable tradition of his family would be that every Ravenwood was to be the shield of the realm until its very last man. And that the lawbreakers would have to face the fury and the loyalty of the raven that would rather cut its own wings than disrespect the word of the King.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '随着岁月的推移，他们的友谊不断增长。当加拉隆建立吉尔尼斯王国时，奥德林被封为雷文郡领主，成为乌鸦林要塞的合法领袖。坐落在边境之地，环抱着辽阔的大海，奥德林将确保他家族中最崇高和令人尊敬的传统是，每一位乌鸦林人都将成为领域的盾牌，守护到最后一个人。而违背法律的人将不得不面对愤怒和忠诚的乌鸦，它宁愿割下自己的翅膀，也不愿不尊重国王的命令。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50599, 'On the day the last sparks of life had left Garaleon\'s body Aldrin became teacher and mentor to the young prince. Not only did he make sure that the heir was ready to take over the legacy of his father but he also employed his own flesh and blood to the young prince and had sworn his entire bloodline to always be in the service of Greymane.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '在加拉隆的身体最后一缕生命之光熄灭的那一天，奥德林成为了年轻王子的导师和指导者。他不仅确保继承人准备好接管父亲的遗产，还将自己的血肉之躯献给了年轻王子，并发誓他的整个血脉将永远为格雷迈恩服务。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50600, 'A bond would be forged further throughout history between these two families. A Greymane will always stand atop the throne of Gilneas and a Ravenwood would always be at their side. ', NULL, NULL, NULL, '这两个家族之间的纽带会在历史的长河中进一步铸造。格雷迈恩家族的成员将永远坐上吉尔尼斯的王座，而乌鸦林家族的人将永远站在他们的身旁。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50601, 'For centuries, the lush forests of Silverpine have been a point of contention in the glorious history of Gilneas, where our nation has had to fend off the greedy and power-hungry mongrels of Dalaran, Alterac, and Lordaeron. Despite our noble efforts to preserve these once tranquil lands, these barbaric foes have transformed them into mass graveyards, leaving many brave Gilnean women widowed due to their insatiable appetite for power.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '数个世纪以来，银松森林一直是吉尔尼斯辉煌历史中的争议焦点，我们的国家不得不抵御达拉然、奥特兰克和洛丹伦等贪婪和渴望权力的势力。尽管我们曾经尽力保护这些曾经宁静的土地，但这些野蛮的敌人已将其变成了大规模的墓地，因为他们对权力的贪婪欲望，许多勇敢的吉尔尼斯女性成了丧偶者。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50602, 'Silverpine rightfully belongs to Gilneas, as it was bestowed upon us by Arathorian prince Lenarol I, and confirmed by our wise and just King Garalon. We have defended Silverpine from countless attacks by the cursed mages of Dalaran and the ruthless brutes of Alterac. Every assault launched against us has been met with unwavering resistance, and we have always stood our ground to defend the land of our forefathers.$B$BSilverlaine Keep, built by Farad Silverlaine, stands as a silent sentinel over these lands, defending them from any enemy who would dare to encroach upon our sovereign territory.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '银松森林理应归属于吉尔尼斯，因为它是由阿拉索的王子莱纳罗一世赐予我们的，并得到了我们睿智公正的国王加拉隆的确认。我们曾经数次击退了达拉然的诅咒法师和奥特兰克的无情野蛮人对银松森林的进攻。每一次对我们发起的袭击都遭遇了坚定的抵抗，我们总是坚守阵地，捍卫我们祖先的土地。$B$B由法拉德·银脉建造的银脉要塞，作为沉默的哨兵屹立在这片土地上，捍卫着这片土地，不容任何敌人侵犯我们的主权领土。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50603, 'The greatest threat to our possession of Silverpine came from the fledgling kingdom of Lordaeron, a kingdom created by the same Arathorian nobles who had previously sought to crush Gilneas. These greedy and unscrupulous men had no qualms about spilling peasant blood to get their hands on the rich and fertile lands of Silverpine.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '对我们对银松森林的拥有权来说，最大的威胁来自刚刚成立的洛丹伦王国，这个王国是由之前曾试图粉碎吉尔尼斯的那些阿拉索贵族创立的。这些贪婪和不择手段的人毫不犹豫地让农民的鲜血流淌，只为了得到银松森林那富饶肥沃的土地。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50604, 'In the year of the Serpent, Lordaerionian forces, led by the vile Prince Arterian Lordanol, crossed the border into Silverpine with over ten thousand heavy troops, four thousand horsemen, and twenty thousand light infantry. They advanced with little resistance until autumn, when they were met with harsh winter conditions and forced to wait until spring.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '在蛇年，由邪恶的阿特里安·洛尔达诺尔王子率领的洛丹伦军队越过边境，带着一万多名重装士兵、四千名骑兵和两万名轻步兵进入了银松森林。他们几乎没有受到什么抵抗就前进了，直到秋天，当他们遭遇严酷的冬季条件，被迫等待春天到来。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50605, 'This was the moment our wise King Veren Greymane had been waiting for. Though our troops numbered only around twenty-five thousand, we were prepared for winter combat much better than the Lordaerionans, who were not accustomed to the harsh climates of the Alterac Mountains.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '这正是我们睿智的国王维伦·格雷迈恩一直在等待的时刻。虽然我们的部队只有大约两万五千人，但我们对冬季作战的准备要比洛丹伦人充分得多，后者并不习惯奥特兰克山脉的严寒气候。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50606, 'When winter struck with all its fury, the Gilnean forces attacked. We cut the supply lines to Lordaeron, starving their soldiers and weakening their morale. They were forced to raid nearby villages and towns for supplies, leaving their main camp with few defenders. Then, during the longest night of the year, under a new moon and in complete darkness, King Veren launched a surprise attack on the Lordaerionan camp.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '当严冬袭来时，吉尔尼斯军队发动了进攻。 我们切断了通往洛丹伦的补给线，使他们的士兵挨饿并削弱了他们的士气。 他们被迫袭击附近的村庄和城镇以获取补给，使得他们的主营几乎没有守军。 然后，在一年中最长的夜晚，在新月和完全黑暗的情况下，维伦国王对洛丹瑞安营地发动了突然袭击。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50607, 'Our soldiers fought with unrivaled zeal and power, with some witnesses claiming that King Veren himself wielded dark powers in battle, manipulating the very blood essence of the fallen Lordaeronian forces.$B$BIn the end, almost all of the Lordaeronian army was either slain or forced to retreat, and Prince Arterian was captured and held for ransom. This was a major victory for Gilneas, and a huge sum of war reparations was paid for Arterian\'s release. He returned to Lordaeron with his tail between his legs, fearful of ever setting foot in Silverpine again.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '我们的士兵以无与伦比的热情和力量战斗，一些目击者声称维伦国王本人在战斗中动用了黑暗力量，操纵了堕落的洛丹伦军队的鲜血本质。$B$B最终，几乎所有的洛丹伦军队要么被杀，要么被迫撤退，阿特瑞安王子被俘虏并索要赎金。这对吉尔尼斯来说是一次重大胜利，为阿特瑞安的释放支付了巨额战争赔款。他颓废地回到洛丹伦，害怕再次踏足银松森林。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50608, 'Despite later losing Silverpine to the Menethils of Lordaeron, Gilneans remain steadfast in our belief that these lands rightfully belong to us. We will continue to strive for the liberation of Silverpine from the vile Menethils and restore it to its rightful owners, the people of Gilneas.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '尽管后来失去了银松森林，让洛丹伦的米奈希尔家族夺走了它，但吉尔尼斯人依然坚定地相信这片土地理应属于我们。我们将继续努力，争取从邪恶的米奈希尔家族手中解放银松森林，并将其归还给其合法所有者，吉尔尼斯的人民。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50609, 'Although the great historians wished to keep this a secret amongst the human kingdoms, it was well known that in the family tree of Ravenwood, blood of Silverlaines was present. What is certain is that the Silverpine Forest was Gilnean lands. The battles that took place on this piece of land forced fate to bond these two dynasties.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '尽管伟大的历史学家希望在人类王国中保守这一秘密，但众所周知，在雷文伍德的家谱中，存在银脉家族的血统。 可以肯定的是，银松森林是吉尔尼斯的土地。 在这片土地上发生的战斗迫使命运将这两个王朝联系在一起。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50610, 'Stories say that in one of the grand battles between Silverpine and Lordaeron, the defense of Silverlaine Keep was led by Baron Caliban I, who had protected his land until the last drop of his blood. It was too late when Lord Casten Ravenwood arrived in the middle of the battle. Caliban had already lost his life.Lady Alnira, daughter of the Baron, was protecting his corpse from the Lordaeronian army that wished to spit one last time on the noble who had sacrificed himself for Gilneas.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '传说中，在银松森林与洛丹伦之间的一场大战中，银脉要塞的防御由巴伦·卡利班一世领导，他保卫自己的土地，直到最后一滴鲜血。当卡斯滕·雷文伍德勋爵在战斗中间赶到时，已经太晚了。卡利班已经失去了生命。巴伦的女儿，阿尔尼拉女士，正在保护他的尸体，阻止洛丹伦军队对这位为吉尔尼斯牺牲的高贵人物最后一次的蔑视。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50611, 'Casten charged with his horse towards the group of soldiers that surrounded Alnira. While landing right next to her, he had realized that the lady wasn\'t as powerless as he had thought. Through the chaos of the battle, she had managed to slip her dagger into the heart of the soldier closest to her. Awed by her initiative, Casten ordered his men to attack. The Lordaeronian army stood no chance; they were slaughtered without a trace.$B$BWhen they returned to Silverlaine Keep, there was no sound of victory, but sheer silence and mourning for the passing of Caliban. Alnira succeeded her father as Baron of the Silverlaine Keep and ruler of Silverpine.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '卡斯滕骑着马冲向包围阿尔尼拉的士兵群。降落在她的身旁时，他意识到这位女士并不像他以前想象的那样无助。在战斗的混乱中，她成功地将匕首刺入了距离她最近的士兵的心脏。对她的果断行动感到敬佩，卡斯滕下令他的部下发动攻击。洛丹伦军队毫无胜算，他们被屠戮得干干净净。$B$B当他们回到银脉要塞时，并没有胜利的喧嚣。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50612, 'Casten didn\'t leave the keep. His heart was stolen by the young lady he had met in the midst of the battle. He had sent ravens to the King, claiming that he would mentor Alnira into becoming a ruler for a short while. For long, he courted her, long enough for her to fall prey to his love. Yet, she did not agree to marriage.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '卡斯滕没有离开要塞。他的心被他在战斗中遇到的年轻女士所俘虏。他向国王派遣了信使，声称他会在一段时间内指导阿尔尼拉成为一名统治者。在此期间，他不断追求她，足够长的时间让她陷入他的爱情之中。然而，她并不同意婚姻。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50613, 'After a time, Casten returned to Ravenwood Keep, but with a heavy heart. He would\'ve done anything for Alnira to accept his marriage proposal, but he had also understood her motives. While married to him, she\'d have to leave Silverlaine Keep and abandon her people.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '一段时间后，卡斯滕带着沉重的心情返回了雷文伍德要塞。他愿意为了让阿尔尼拉接受他的求婚而付出一切，但他也明白了她的动机。如果嫁给他，她就必须离开银脉要塞，抛弃她的人民。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50614, 'It wasn\'t long before the Lordaeron army struck a second time. When Casten heard about the sudden invasion, he rushed to his King to ask for him to be allowed to aid Alnira. Although the king would\'ve had Casten remain in the kingdom and assured him that Alnira would be fine, Casten still pleaded. He had confessed to the King the love he carried for her and that she had sent him news of being with child days before. The King allowed Casten and his men to leave, and the Lordaeron forces were decimated.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '没过多久，洛丹伦军队第二次发动袭击。当卡斯滕听说突然的入侵时，他赶紧去找国王，请求被允许协助阿尔尼拉。尽管国王希望卡斯滕留在王国，而且向他保证阿尔尼拉会没事，但卡斯滕仍然请求。他向国王坦白了自己对阿尔尼拉的爱，还告诉他几天前她发来的怀孕消息。国王允许卡斯滕和他的部下离开，洛丹伦军队遭到重创。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50615, 'When the battle ended, in a last attempt, Casten asked Alnira to marry him once again. Overcome by emotion, she fell to her knees and started to weep. Both of them had a long discussion about the future. They decided not to get married, and the love they carried for each other was enough. Months later, Alnira gave birth to twins. One of them was to live with her and continue the legacy of Silverlaine, while the other was to live with his father and continue the line of Ravenwood.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '战斗结束后，在最后一次尝试中，卡斯滕再次向阿尔尼拉求婚。被情感压倒，她跪在地上哭泣。他们俩进行了一场长时间的关于未来的讨论。他们决定不结婚，他们之间的爱已经足够。几个月后，阿尔尼拉生下了一对双胞胎。其中一个将与她一起生活，继续银脉的传承，而另一个将与父亲一起生活，继续雷文伍德的血脉。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50616, 'They never married someone else. Because of that, both of their children were seen as bastards by many at the time. The truth was only revealed after Alnira\'s death, which had outlived Casten. The two brothers had a tough road to adjust to at first but with time their relationship grew and was upheld for generations to comeю.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '他们从未与其他人结婚。因此，他们的孩子在当时被许多人视为私生子。真相直到阿尔尼拉去世后才揭示出来，她比卡斯滕活得更久。两个兄弟一开始适应起来的路很艰难，但随着时间的推移，他们的关系不断加深，并在未来的几代人中得到了维系。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50617, 'On the eve days of the Third War, under a clear night sky, King Genn Greymane beheld his realm upon his high terrace. From the shadow of his great wall there came a dark raven on a cold wind; it perched beside the proud King, and in a flash of green, its likeness became that of a hooded man.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '在第三次战争的前夜，在晴朗的夜空下，吉尔尼斯国王吉恩·格雷迈恩站在高台上，俯瞰着他的领土。从他巍峨城墙的阴影中，随着寒风来了一只黑暗的乌鸦；它停在骄傲的国王旁边，瞬间变化成了一个戴着兜帽的人的模样，散发出绿色的光芒。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50618, 'King Genn was nigh to hurl the sorcerous intruder from the balcony, when the latter bowed and begged forgiveness. He would not give his name, only prophecies and warnings. He spoke of the northern plague, of the savage orcs, of demons and living dead and the return of a most ancient evil.$B$BHe told the King to flee west, to the uncharted lands of Kalimdor.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '吉恩国王差点把这位魔法入侵者从阳台上扔下去，后者鞠躬并请求宽恕。 他不愿透露自己的名字，只透露预言和警告。 他谈到了北方瘟疫、野蛮的兽人、恶魔和活死人以及最古老的邪恶的回归。$B$B他告诉国王向西逃亡，前往卡利姆多的未知土地。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50619, 'Laughter was the King\'s response. \'Flight is a craven\'s course.\' He answered \'Look to my wall and do not marvel at the strength of its stone, rather of the men who guard its ramparts. Gilnean men! Hard as iron, brave like lions. Go, tell them that their home is not worth defending. Tell them to make refugees of their wives, beggars of their children. Go! There you shall find Gilneas\' answer!\'', NULL, NULL, NULL, '国王的回应是笑声。 “飞行是懦夫的必经之路。” 他回答说：“看看我的城墙，不要惊叹它的石头的力量，而要惊叹那些守卫它的壁垒的人。” 吉尔尼斯人！ 坚如铁，勇如狮。 去吧，告诉他们，他们的家园不值得保卫。 告诉他们让他们的妻子成为难民，让他们的孩子成为乞丐。 去！ 在那里你会找到吉尔尼斯的答案！', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50620, 'The Prophet bowed and left the way he came.$B$BYet as the months drew on, each of the stranger\'s prophecies turned to reality. First the return of the orcs, then the coming of the plague. When word spread that the marvellous city of Stratholme had been put to the torch, King Genn tightened his resolve and sealed his gates to all outsiders.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '先知鞠躬离开了，就像他来的时候一样。$B$B然而，随着时间的推移，这位陌生人的每一条预言都变成了现实。首先是兽人的归来，然后是瘟疫的到来。当传出奇迹般的城市斯坦索姆已被火炬点燃的消息时，国王吉恩坚定了决心，关闭了城门，不再接纳任何外来者。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50621, 'There were those in the King\'s council who protested at his edict. Chief of these dissidents was the Crown Prince himself, Liam, who brought the news of Lady Jaina Proudmoore gathering the survivors of Lordaeron and sailing west to Kalimdor. He petitioned for his royal father to send a honor guard to escort the defenseless refugees. But the King refused, on account that any pestilence borne by the Lordaeronians risked spreading back to Gilneas.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '国王的顾问中有些人对他的法令表示抗议。这些反对派中的首领是王储利亚姆，他带来了吉安娜·普罗德摩尔夫人将洛丹伦幸存者聚集起来，向西航行前往卡利姆多的消息。他请求王父派遣荣誉卫队护送这些无助的难民。但国王拒绝了，因为洛丹伦人身上携带的任何瘟疫都有传播回吉尔尼斯的风险。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50622, 'Left with no other choice, Prince Liam went to find support among the lords of Gilneas without his father\'s knowledge.$B$BFew shared his views, but of these, Lord Darius Ravenwood and Lord Gerold of Gelnor were the most influential. While Lord Ravenwood readied a fleet in secret, Gerold assembled a force of stout Gelnorian dwarves and men to volunteer as the promised honor guard.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '利亚姆王子别无选择，在父亲不知情的情况下，前往吉尔尼斯领主那里寻求支持。$B$B 很少有人同意他的观点，但其中最有影响力的是大流士·拉文伍德勋爵和吉尔诺的杰罗德勋爵。 当拉文伍德领主秘密准备一支舰队时，杰洛德集结了一支由强壮的吉尔诺瑞亚矮人和人类组成的部队，自愿担任承诺的仪仗队。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50623, 'Thus was the Gilneas Brigade born, named by Prince Liam with full honors on the Gilnean shores. By the time King Genn uncovered the plot, the ships, the soldiers and their supplies were far past the horizon. Harsh punishment fell upon all the plotters, the Crown Prince included, but the warriors found their way into the service of Jaina Proudmoore regardless. At her side they are said to remain, loyal unto the bitter end.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '吉尔尼斯旅就这样诞生了，由利亚姆王子命名，在吉尔尼斯海岸获得了充分的荣誉。 当吉恩国王发现这个阴谋时，船只、士兵和物资已经远离地平线。 包括王储在内的所有密谋者都受到了严厉的惩罚，但战士们无论如何都会为吉安娜·普罗德摩尔服务。 据说他们会留在她身边，忠诚到最后。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50624, 'Following the disastrous War of the Three Hammers, the hill dwarven clans sworn to the Wildhammers deserted their old homes of Grim Batol, Kalvanost and Dun Kithas, and wandered the northern realms in search of new lands to call their own.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '在灾难性的三锤之战之后，宣誓效忠蛮锤氏族的山地矮人抛弃了格瑞姆巴托、卡尔瓦诺斯特和丹基萨斯的故乡，在北方王国中流浪，寻找属于自己的新土地。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50625, 'Though most Wildhammers settled in what would soon become Aerie Peak, the dwarves of Kalvanost and Dun Kithas continued their search, parting from their brethren and often straying into human territories.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '尽管大多数蛮锤氏族定居在后来成为鹰巢山的地方，但卡尔瓦诺斯特和邓基塞斯的矮人们继续他们的探索，与兄弟们分道扬镳，常常涉足人类领地。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50626, 'There, the mighty Sky King of Kalvanost, Morgryn, made war upon the humans of Lordaeron and Alterac, reaping their wealth to restore his own.$B$BThe fairer Sky King of Dun Kithas, Redoran, flew instead from thence far into the west, until he came to the Gilnean city of Gelnor.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '在那里，强大的卡尔瓦诺斯特天空之王莫格林向洛丹伦和奥特兰克的人类发动了战争，掠夺了他们的财富以恢复自己的财富。$B$B更美丽的丹基萨斯天空之王雷多兰从那里飞向遥远的西方 ，直到他来到了吉尔尼斯城格尔诺。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50627, 'Redoran gifted many trinkets of his people to the Gilneans, which they treasured, awed by the artisanship of dwarven-craft.$B$BRichest of Redoran\'s gifts was a bejeweled mithril crown he gifted to the ruling Greymane Queen, Elaena the Good. So charmed was Elaena that throughout her reign she never again unwearied her head.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '雷多兰赠送了许多他人民的小玩意儿给吉尔尼斯人，他们对矮人工艺的技艺感到惊叹，并且珍视这些礼物。$B$B雷多兰最富有的礼物是一顶镶宝石的秘银王冠，他将其赠送给当时的吉尔尼斯女王埃莱娜善良女王。埃莱娜对这顶王冠深感倾心，以至于在她的统治期间，她再也没有卸下过这顶王冠。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50628, 'When Redoran and his people made ready to depart, they were halted by Queen Elaena who, for their generosity to the people of Gilneas, gifted them a place in Gelnor and to Redoran a seat at her court. The dwarves were glad to accept and Redoran ever shared Elaena\'s trust and council.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '当雷多兰和他的人民准备出发时，他们被埃莱娜女王拦住了，女王出于对吉尔尼斯人民的慷慨，赐予他们在格尔诺的一个地方，并给了雷多兰在她宫廷的一个席位。 矮人们很高兴接受，雷多兰也一直分享埃莱娜的信任和建议。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50629, 'After over two centuries, dwarves and humans in Gelnor have adopted many of each other\'s customs.$B$BThe dwarves have taken to the worship of the Light, albeit in hewn caverns of carven stone rather than churches, and the humans became excellent wood-carvers and gryphon riders, if more inclined to long lances rather than thunderhammers.$B$BIt is said that to this day, dwarves and humans live there in Gelnor as one Gilnean kin, their fates entwined until the breaking of the world.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '经过两个多世纪，吉尔诺的矮人和人类各自采纳了对方的许多习俗。矮人开始崇拜光明，虽然不是在教堂里，而是在雕刻石头的洞穴中，而人类则成为了优秀的木雕工和狮鹫骑士，虽然更倾向于长矛而不是雷霆之锤。据说直到今天，矮人和人类在吉尔诺生活，成为一个吉尔尼斯的族群，他们的命运纠结在一起，直到世界的崩裂。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50630, 'Hierophant Joshua the Redeemer was the holiest man that ever walked the land of Gilneas: Through his blessed sermons he brought salvation to our country, illuminating our souls in the grace of the Holy Light. May our elder brother rest in sacred peace, and when the darkest of days fall upon our city, may his hallowed memory bring solace to our troubled hearts.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '\"救赎者\"乔舒亚大神官是曾经走过吉尔尼斯土地上最神圣的人：通过他祝福的布道，他给我们的国家带来了救赎，用神圣之光的恩宠照亮了我们的灵魂。愿我们的长兄在神圣的宁静中安息，在我们的城市陷入最黑暗的时刻时，愿他神圣的记忆为我们困扰的心灵带来安慰。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50631, 'The sky darkened over the lands of Gilneas. Lord Darius summoned all the minor nobles that were loyal to him at his court. A visit from Gilneas City was soon due.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '吉尔尼斯的土地上阴云密布。达瑞斯勋爵在他的庭院里召集了所有忠于他的次要贵族。吉尔尼斯城的一次访问即将到来。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50632, 'Much had changed in our lands since death claimed our Queen, Mia. The Alteraci parasites have spit poison in the ears of the King, claiming it was Lord Ravenwood who pulled the nefarious strings.$B$BAnd yet, it was also by their treacherous deeds that Ravenwood\'s name was cleared in the blood of betrayers.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '自从死神夺去了我们的女王米娅，我们的土地发生了很多变化。奥特兰克的寄生虫在国王的耳边吐毒，声称是雷文伍德勋爵在背后操纵。$B$B然而，正是因为他们的背信弃义的行为，雷文伍德的名字在叛徒的鲜血中得到了洗刷。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50633, '\"Are you certain, my lord? Would the Harlows really be the head of this vicious plot?\"$B$B\"Without a doubt, my dear Caliban. It seems that through their malice they have come to thieve the governing of these lands. They must have taken advantage of Genn\'s broken heart and twisted his mind, perhaps even his body. There is no telling what this illness they claim hit the King truly is.\"$B$BA silence, a sister with death herself claimed the lord\'s grand hall.$B$BRegan Willowfield, messenger of the new Harlow Regent-Lords, had arrived.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '\"您确定吗，大人？难道哈洛家族真的是这个恶毒阴谋的幕后主使？\" $B$B \"毫无疑问，亲爱的卡利班。看来他们通过恶意已经开始窃取这片土地的统治权。他们一定趁着吉恩心碎的时候扭曲了他的心灵，甚至可能连他的身体也被扭曲。我们无法确定他们所声称的那种袭击国王的疾病的真正情况。\" $B$B 一阵寂静，一位宛如死神本人的姐妹走进了领主的大厅。 $B$B 新的哈洛摄政领主的使者瑞甘·威洛菲尔德已经到来。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50634, 'The cold gates of the keep opened to the prideful messenger. His head did not bow, he offered no greeting, he sneered before the seat of the lord \"Lord Darius Ravenwood, master of Ravenwood Keep and the lands of Ravenshire. I, Regan Willowfield, have come to relay a message from the new rulers of Gilneas.\"$B$B\"And to what do we owe this honor, unlanded lord and honorless knight?\"$B$BRegan frowned, \"How tall you stand in your chair, Ravenwood. And yet the message I bring is higher than both your hubris and vanity.\"', NULL, NULL, NULL, '冰冷的城门向傲慢的使者敞开。他的头没有低下，他没有致以问候，他在领主的座位前冷笑着说道：“达瑞斯·雷文伍德勋爵，雷文伍德要塞和雷文希尔领地的主人。我，雷根·威洛菲尔德，来传达吉尔尼斯的新统治者的消息。”$B$B“那么我们应该如何感谢这份荣誉，无土地的领主和无荣誉的骑士？”$B$B雷根皱了皱眉，“你坐在椅子上显得多么高大，雷文伍德。然而，我带来的消息比你的傲慢和虚荣更高。”', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50635, 'Murmurs of disdain rose from the court.$B$B\"And what message has the filth of Alterac bid you here relay, proud Regan?\"$B$B\"I\'d measure my words, Lord.\"$B$B\"I shall measure your neck with this sword were you to mutter another slight towards my liege.\" One of the courtiers claimed.$B$BDarius raised his hand to bid calm to his loyal friend.$B$B\"Apologies for my man\'s boldness. Fealty and friendship binds us, I am sure you understand. I yearn to hear the gracious words of the Regent-Lords.\"', NULL, NULL, NULL, '法庭上传来了不满的低语声。$B$B“那么，奥特兰克的污秽之辈派你前来传达什么消息，骄傲的雷根？”$B$B“我会掂量我的话，勋爵。”$B$B“如果你再对我尊主发表一次轻蔑的言论，我将用这把剑掂量你的脖子。”法庭上的一名人声言道。$B$B达瑞斯举起手示意他忠诚的朋友平静下来。$B$B“为我的人的大胆道歉。忠诚和友谊将我们紧紧相连，我相信您能理解。我渴望听到摄政王的慷慨之言。”', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50636, 'Regan cleared his throat: \"Their Highnesses wish to express their displeasure towards your absence at their naming ceremony. They wish nothing but peace with the Shield of Gilneas. They claim that in these harsh times we must not be at odds.\"$B$B\"And what of the army within my lands? I doubt they are here to serve me.\"$B$B\"Precisely that, my Lord. They are a gift from Lord Mortimer, were you to accept his request to offer your daughter\'s hand to him.\"$B$BLord Darius\' silence froze the blood inside Regan\'s veins.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '雷根清了清嗓子：“陛下们希望表达他们对您在他们的加冕仪式上缺席的不满。他们与吉尔尼斯的盾牌只愿和平相处。他们声称在这个艰难的时刻，我们不应该争斗。”$B$B“那么我的领地内的军队呢？我怀疑他们不是来为我服务的。”$B$B“正是如此，我的勋爵。他们是莫蒂默勋爵的礼物，如果您接受他的请求，将您的女儿嫁给他。”$B$B达瑞斯勋爵的沉默让雷根的血液凝结。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50637, 'Before either could speak, Viscount Laurion came before Darius, kneeling and offering him a bloodied sword. \"This blade was stained by their army\'s commander.\"$B$BDarius eyed Laurion: \"And what of the others?\"$B$B\"Those that surrendered were taken to the cellars. The others were chained and beaten for blood.\"$B$BRegan shook: \"My Lo- Lord, what is the meaning of this?\"', NULL, NULL, NULL, '在任何人发表言辞之前，洛里昂子爵跪在达瑞斯面前，递上一把满是鲜血的剑。“这把刀被他们的军队指挥官染血了。”$B$B达瑞斯盯着劳里昂：“其他人呢？”$B$B“那些投降的被带到了地窖里。其他人被铐住，被打得浑身是血。”$B$B雷根颤抖着：“我—我，勋，勋爵，这是什么意思？”', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50638, 'Darius claimed the sword from Laurion\'s hands and pointed it at Regan: \"Take the two at his side and those chained to the walls of the keep and hang them. Had you come to me with humility, Regan, I would\'ve spared your life, but alas. Laurion, find a post, three nails and a hammer, then crucify this mouthpiece. The Harlows will feel fear and even the Light itself shall tremble at my fury!\"', NULL, NULL, NULL, '达瑞斯从洛里昂的手中接过剑，将其指向雷根：“带走他身边的两个人和那些被铐在要塞墙上的人，将他们吊死。雷根，如果你以谦卑的态度来找我，我本可以饶你一命，可惜了。洛里昂，找一根柱子，三颗钉子和一把锤子，然后将这个传话者钉在上面。哈洛家族将感受到恐惧，甚至光明本身都会因为我的愤怒而颤抖！”', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50639, 'And so the First Rebellion began. Darius gathered all the soldiers he had left. The common folk under his rule were both inspired by his love for his lands and fearful of his brutality. Yet beyond fear laid respect. They knew and know that desperate times call for desperate deeds.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '第一次叛乱就这样开始了。达瑞斯召集了他剩下的所有士兵。 他统治下的普通民众既被他对土地的热爱所鼓舞，又对他的残暴感到恐惧。 然而，除了恐惧之外，还有尊重。 他们知道并且知道，绝望的时刻需要绝望的行动。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50640, 'The battle was won by the righteous rebels. But with a heavy toll. Ravenwood Keep was destroyed, and all who died on its soil could never recognize ally from foe, cursed into vengeful wraiths by the dark magics of the Alteraci Harlow scum.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '正义的叛军赢得了这场战斗，但代价沉重。雷文伍德要塞被摧毁，所有死在那片土地上的人再也无法分辨盟友和敌人，被奥特兰克的哈洛家族的黑暗魔法诅咒变成了复仇的怨灵。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50641, 'A treaty was signed between Lord Ravenwood and the Harlows. One in which Darius surrendered his daughter, Elena, to marry the Harlow lordling. Elena sacrificed herself so that Darius could purchase a tenuous truce to bide his time.$B$BBut Greymane shall always sit upon our throne, we will make sure of it. The Gate will fall, and we shall find aid in old allegiances. We will never surrender our country.$B$BFind with your eyes the tallest tree in the land. That, is how tall our great people stand.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '达瑞斯与哈洛家族签署了一项条约。根据这项条约，达瑞斯将他的女儿埃莉娜嫁给哈洛家族的一名年轻领主。埃莉娜为了让达瑞斯能够购买脆弱的休战时间而牺牲了自己。$B$B但是格雷迈恩将永远坐在我们的王座上，我们将确保如此。城门将会倒下，我们会在旧有的盟约中寻求帮助。我们绝不会放弃我们的国家。$B$B用你的眼睛寻找这片土地上最高的树。这就是我们伟大人民的高度。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50642, 'Through decades of intensive research, it has become irrefutable that what is conventionally known as Blood Magic does not originate from our World. Those who profess to have attained mastery in this form of spellcasting are, in essence, akin to orcish warlocks, harnessing their abilities from the Twisting Nether itself.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '经过数十年的深入研究，已经不容置疑，传统上所称的鲜血魔法并非源自我们的世界。那些声称已经掌握了这种法术形式的人，本质上类似于兽人术士，他们从扭曲虚空中获得他们的能力。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50643, 'The task that consumed many challenging years was discovering the source of this type of magic. It was evident that it necessitated fuel, in the form of blood, and granted spellcasters access to extraplanar powers. What was unclear, however, was how the link to this \"Blood Dimension\" was established.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '耗费了许多充满挑战性的年份的任务是发现这种类型的魔法的来源。很明显，它需要以血液的形式作为燃料，并赋予咒语施法者访问外部位面的力量。然而，不清楚的是，如何建立与这个“血之维度”的联系。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50644, 'Initially, I delved into the practices of the Gurubashi Trolls and their Blooddrinkers, but their methods proved to be different. Their magic was not connected to this Blood Dimension, as it derived its potency from their Blood God, much like most of the troll magicks. Hence, I quickly abandoned this line of inquiry.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '起初，我深入研究了古拉巴什巨魔及其血饮者的实践，但他们的方法被证明与此不同。他们的魔法与这个“血之维度”没有关联，因为它的力量来自于他们的血神，就像大多数巨魔的魔法一样。因此，我很快放弃了这一调查线索。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50645, 'As always, our High Elven comrades proved invaluable. Their ancient manuscripts, predating the legendary Sundering - if one chooses to believe such lore - detailed their spellcasters drawing power from the Blood Dimension, referred to as Vorgendor in their language. The rites mentioned appeared to align with my quest. The use of prodigious amounts of blood could heighten physical strength, intellect, and agility of the practitioner. However, according to the manuscripts, these rituals carried many deleterious effects, including but not limited to madness, visions, and transforming into wolf-like creatures.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '一如既往，我们的高等精灵同伴证明是无价之宝。他们的古老手稿，早于传说中的“分裂时代”——如果有人愿意相信这样的传说——详细描述了他们的法术施法者从“血之维度”中汲取力量，他们的语言中称之为“沃根多尔”。文中提到的仪式似乎与我的探索相吻合。使用大量的血液可以提升施法者的体力、智力和敏捷。然而，根据手稿，这些仪式会带来许多有害的影响，包括但不限于疯狂、幻象，以及变成狼一般的生物。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50646, 'Over time, their experiments led to disastrous consequences, as their bodies and minds were twisted and corrupted by the dark energies they had unleashed. The survivors were hunted down and banished from their homeland, their knowledge of Blood Magic lost to the ages.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '随着时间的推移，他们的实验导致了灾难性的后果，他们的身体和心智被他们释放出的黑暗能量扭曲和腐化。幸存者被追捕并被驱逐出他们的家园，他们关于鲜血魔法的知识被埋藏在岁月的尘埃中。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50647, 'It was apparent that I had to undertake the investigation myself. The specifics of how I acquired the necessary blood for the rituals need not concern the reader, other than to note that it was accomplished without harm to innocent individuals. <The book now describes Blood Magic rituals with detail.>', NULL, NULL, NULL, '很明显，我必须亲自进行调查。我获得所需的血液进行仪式的具体方法不必让读者关心，除了注意到这是在不伤害无辜人员的情况下完成的。<这本书现在详细描述了血魔法仪式。>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50648, 'It is imperative to emphasize that these practices should be banished and proscribed. The agony I endured was indescribable, and the benefits meager, not to mention the grotesque visions of a world consumed by the Emerald Flame. I have documented this knowledge purely to caution future generations from engaging in these activities, and I fervently hope that the Kirin Tor will forever safeguard these secrets.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '强调这些实践应该被禁止和制止是非常必要的。我所经历的痛苦无法形容，而所获的好处微不足道，更不用说那些关于被翡翠之焰吞噬的世界的怪诞幻象。我记录下这些知识纯粹是为了警告后代不要参与这些活动，我真诚地希望克尔苏加德会永远保护这些机密。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50649, '<The first half of the journal is entirely unremarkable. A young man\'s struggles with growing up, supporting his family and their farm, making a living, dreams and aspirations, budding love, his favorite food, pets and horses...>$B$B<Rather suddenly, the neat ink handwriting is replaced with a much thicker writing. Black and smudged, as though scribed with a ghostly fingertip.>', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<日记的前半部分完全普通。一个年轻人成长的挣扎，支持家庭和农场，谋生，梦想和抱负，初生的爱情，他最喜欢的食物，宠物和马匹...>$B$B<突然间，整齐的墨水字迹被更浓的字迹所取代。黑色而且有点模糊，仿佛是用幽灵般的指尖书写的。>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50650, 'DAY 1$B$BThe boy was so delicious looking in his innocence. We allowed him to sleep, sleep so softly beneath my willow tree. He was warmed by the fire, though our bodies could never warm him now. We watched his nose flare with each youthful breath.$B$BAnd how were we repaid? The boy kicked over the campfire to put it out. In the heat of summer, the fire spread, scorching my mushroom rings, the bark of my willow, my delicate grass blades...', NULL, NULL, NULL, '第1天$B$B这个少年在他的天真中看起来是如此美味。我们允许他入睡，在我的柳树下如此轻柔地入睡。他在火光的温暖下，尽管我们的身体现在永远无法让他暖和。我们看着他年轻的呼吸中鼻子一阵阵扩张。$B$B而我们得到了什么回报？这个少年踢翻了营火把它扑灭。在盛夏的热浪下，火势蔓延，烧焦了我的蘑菇环，我的柳树皮，我娇嫩的草叶...', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50651, 'DAY 4$B$BWe mourned, we sang songs of bereavement. It was my willow, so it is my vengeance. I followed his scent back to his farm. I observed the boy. He seemed to forget it already. I would make him remember.$B$BAt night, I so softly tapped against the window. Rapped against it. I smiled. I waved to him through the veil. Oh, the sweat of his brow! Oh, the fear in his eyes! Oh the strained beating of his heart!', NULL, NULL, NULL, '第4天$B$B我们哀悼，我们唱着悲伤的歌曲。那是我的柳树，所以这是我的复仇。我追踪着他的气味回到他的农场。我观察着那个少年。他似乎已经忘记了。我会让他记得的。$B$B在夜晚，我轻轻地敲打窗户。敲打着它。我微笑着。我透过窗帘向他招手。噢，他额头上的汗水！ 哦，他的眼中充满了恐惧！ 哦，他的心脏紧张地跳动着！', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50652, 'DAY 15$B$BHe has barely slept. I always remind him I am watching. A scratching at the door, a flickering of the candles, a touch of breath against the nape of the neck, a pair of eyes in the fog. I can feel his mind growing tired, delirious, day by day.$B$BSo tired was he, he fell asleep on his feet. I allowed myself into his mind, smothered his thoughts, drowned his hopes. His body temperature dropped so deliciously. I will have to indulge myself in his dreams more and more...', NULL, NULL, NULL, '第15天$B$B他几乎没有入睡。我总是提醒他我在看着。门口有刮擦声，烛光闪烁，脖子后面有一丝气息，雾中有一双眼睛。我能感觉到他的心智日复一日地变得疲惫，错乱。$B$B他如此疲倦，竟然站着睡着了。我让自己进入他的思想，窒息他的思想，淹没他的希望。他的体温下降得如此美妙。我将不得不越来越多地沉溺于他的梦境中...', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50653, 'DAY 32$B$BHis parents and friends know something is wrong. I told him not to tell. If he tells, that would make me so very upset and angry. I would be forced to extend his curse onto those he loves most. I would hate to have to do that. His parents are so very old, they would not make good dance partners. And his little love is not my type.$B$B I ran my invisible, cold fingers through his golden mane as he returned home, today. It was barely dusk, and I had not appeared to him so early as of yet. He did not even run. He is growing accepting of his fate.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '第32天$B$B他的父母和朋友知道有些事情不对劲。我告诉他不要告诉任何人。如果他告诉了，那会让我非常不高兴和愤怒。我将不得不将他的诅咒延伸到他最亲爱的人身上。我不愿意这样做。他的父母已经很老了，他们不适合做我的舞伴。而他那个小小的情人也不是我的类型。$B$B今天，他回家的时候，我用我的无形、冰冷的手指穿过他金色的鬃毛。此刻才刚刚黄昏，我还没有像现在这样早出现在他面前。他甚至没有逃跑。他正在逐渐接受他的命运。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50654, 'DAY 56$B$BHe is almost gone. The boy has bags under his eyes, his hair is greying, he stutters and dares not to raise his eyes above floor level. His will is almost broken. I have begun whispering to him during the day as well as the night now. Join us... join us...$B$BHe will join us. He will join us around my willow. He will enter our circle. He will dance the black waltz. He will dance with us forever, and ever, and ever, and ever, and ever, and ever, and...$B$B<The same words are repeated for fifty pages.>', NULL, NULL, NULL, '第56天$B$B他几乎完全消失了。这个男孩眼袋深陷，头发变灰，口吃，不敢抬起眼睛超过地板的高度。他的意志几乎被摧毁了。我已经开始在白天和夜晚对他低语。加入我们...加入我们...$B$B他会加入我们。他会加入我们，在我的柳树周围。他将进入我们的圈子。他将跳黑色的华尔兹。他将永远、永远、永远、永远、永远、永远、永远地与我们一起跳...$B$B<同样的字句在五十页中重复出现。>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50655, 'Eldre\'Thalas was founded, in part, as a vault for Queen Azshara\'s most prized possessions and secrets. The need for local education quickly became a necessity, but the city lacked a formal ruler capable of establishing this.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '艾德萨拉斯的建立在一定程度上是作为艾萨拉女王最珍贵的财产和秘密的储藏室。 当地教育的需求很快成为一种必要，但这座城市缺乏一个能够建立这种教育的正式统治者。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50656, 'Her cousin, Tortheldrin, was tasked with ruling the city in her name, and he had the royal title of Prince bestowed upon him for such a sacred duty.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '她的表亲托瑟尓德林被委以代表她统治城市的任务，并且他因此神圣的职责被授予皇家头衔——王子。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50657, 'Prince Tortheldrin was aware of the need for local education, and so the construction of an academy began in the hills near Eldre\'Thalas, dedicated to all manner of subjects deemed important. The Academy itself was heralded as rivalling Nar\'Thalas near Suramar for majesty: large edifices and towers reflecting the splendor of its creators.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '托瑟尓德林王子意识到当地教育的需要，因此在艾德萨拉斯附近的山丘上开始建造一所学院，致力于各种被认为重要的科目。这所学院本身被誉为与苏拉玛附近的纳塔拉斯相媲美的宏伟建筑：大型建筑和塔楼反映了创造者的辉煌。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50658, 'The Academy was named Ronae\'Thalas, meaning Land of Tranquility. It came to house a fount of power connected to the Well of Eternity, and a great library containing countless tomes.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '这所学院被命名为罗奈萨拉斯意为“宁静之地”。它拥有一个与永恒之井相连的强大力量源泉，以及一个包含无数卷轴的巨大图书馆。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50659, 'As the population of Eldre\'Thalas increased, young nobles were taught the arcane arts within Ronae\'Thalas\' halls. To have been educated here was a renowned mark of prestige and honor.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '随着艾德雷萨拉斯人口的增加，年轻的贵族们在罗奈萨拉斯的大厅里学习奥术。 在这里接受教育是一种声望和荣誉的著名标志。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (50660, 'Ronae\'Thalas has rested in the hills for over a Millenia now, and its prestige is known far and wide. Even the furthest reaches of the empire reflect our Queen\'s greatness with such wondrous places.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '罗奈萨拉斯已经在山丘上休憩了千年之久，其声望远近闻名。 即使是帝国最遥远的地方，也可以看到我们女王的伟大通过这些美妙的地方得以体现。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (80150, 'Hey bub! It\'s me, Grizzie, from Undermine. Remember me?\n\nI\'m writing this here letter to let you know I saw you swinging that weapon at them fools that tried to give you the gutter. It reminded me of the good ol\' days when we were just little runts, and that time you saved me from that hobgoblin!\n\nThanks to you, I trained hard and became a big-shot bruiser, and now I\'m teaching other goblins how to smack. Come by later and let me teach you a thing or two about how to use that thing you\'re flailing around. Make sure you bring your coin purse!', NULL, NULL, NULL, '\n嘿，老兄！是我，格里兹，来自地底城。还记得我吗？\n\n我写这封信是为了让你知道，我看到你向那些试图让你陷入困境的傻瓜挥舞着武器。 这让我想起了我们还是小混混时的美好时光，那一次你从那个大角魔手中救了我！\n\n多亏了你，我努力训练，成了个大人物的打手，现在我正在教其他地精如何打拳。 稍后过来，让我教你一两件事，关于如何使用你正在挥舞的那个东西。记得带上你的金币袋子哦！', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (80151, 'Thief! Scoundrel! Son of a Gnome!\n\nDon\'t think I didn\'t hear you were skulking around up here, $N. You got some nerve showing your face in the same operation as Leyti Quicktongue.\n\nYou stole my gig, the greatest heist this side of Azeroth! I would have been filthy rich and vanished without a trace!\n\nUntil you bungled in and screwed everything up. You went and got yourself caught, and I\'ll bet you\'re not laboring for Venture Co. because you wanted to.\n\nNo matter. Come by the collapsed cave and give me back the money you owe me! Maybe you could learn a thing or two from a real Rogue.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '小偷！流氓！该死的侏儒之子！\n\n别以为我没听说你在这附近潜伏，$N。你真是胆大包天，竟然敢和莱蒂·快舌一起出现。\n\n你偷走了我的买卖，这可是整个艾泽拉斯这边最大的一次劫案！我本可以暴富然后消失得无影无踪！\n\n可你却闯了进来，把一切都搞砸了。你自己都给抓住了，我敢打赌你也不是愿意为了风险公司干活的。\n\n不过没关系。到那个塌陷的洞穴来，把你欠我的钱还给我！也许你能从一个真正的潜行者身上学到一些东西。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (80152, 'For $N:\n\nI\'m Mayten Boomrifle, the local big game hunter. Believe it or not, I was going to be on the hunt in Stranglethorn Vale with Hemmet Nesingwary himself. Unfortunately, my debts to the Venture Co. dragged me out here to this dirt hole.\n\nThere\'s not much to shoot out here but buzzards or crows, but that doesn\'t mean you shouldn\'t try to be a proper marksman. I saw the way you were lining up your shots earlier, and I think you could benefit from training with me. For just a few coins, you could learn to be a real sharpshooter.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '致$N：\n\n我是梅坦·炸炮，这里的本地猎人。信不信由你，我本来要和赫米特·奈辛瓦里一起去荆棘谷狩猎的。可惜，我欠了风险公司的债，被逼到了这个破地方。\n\n这里没什么可打的，只有秃鹫或乌鸦，但这并不意味着你不应该努力成为一名合格的神射手。我看到你之前是如何对准目标开枪的，我认为你可以从和我一起训练中受益。只需花点小钱，你就可以学会成为一名真正的射手高手。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (80153, 'Heya, $N! The name\'s Wizette Icewhistle.\n\nI hear you got big brains and a knack for magic just like yours truly. One day you wished so hard you could blow something up, your hands just caught fire! Am I right?\n\nAmazing what you can do if you just think it hard enough. Like this whole operation full of lunk-heads spontaneously bursting into flame. It\'s so miserable in this hole.\n\nCome pay me a visit and let\'s talk magic! Teaching you some new spells might distract me from thinking this place on fire.\n\nOh, don\'t forget to bring some coin!', NULL, NULL, NULL, '嘿，$N！我叫维泽特·冰哨。\n\n我听说你和我一样有聪明的头脑和魔法天赋。 有一天，你非常希望能炸掉一些东西，但你的手却着火了！ 我对吗？\n\n只要你认为足够努力，你就能做出令人惊叹的事情。 就像这整个充满笨蛋的行动一样，自发地爆发出火焰。 这坑里真是惨不忍睹啊\n\n来拜访我，让我们谈谈魔法吧！ 教你一些新咒语可能会分散我的注意力，让我不再思考这个地方着火了。\n\n哦，别忘了带一些硬币！', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (80154, 'Hail, $N. I am Amri Demondeal, dark arts practitioner extraordinaire.\n\nWhen I first saw you toiling with the other dregs, I felt an aura similar to mine. I think you\'ve got the chops for summoning demons and conjuring felfire!\n\nI am intrigued, and wish to see what you\'re capable of. Meet me in my cave and let\'s see if you\'ve got what it takes.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '万岁，$N。我是阿姆里·恶魔交易者，黑暗艺术的超级行家。\n\n当我第一次看到你和其他废物一起苦干的时候，我感受到了与我相似的氛围。我认为你有能力召唤恶魔和施展邪能之火！\n\n我很感兴趣，希望看看你有什么本事。来我的洞穴找我吧，我们看看你是否有这个能力。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (80226, 'Greetings, $N!\n\nMy name is Rubinah Sunsworn! I have watched your exploits with interest. You are a fine ranger, but the loss of our homeland has left your training incomplete.\n\nTwenty years ago, during the Second War, the Farstriders planted a seed from our homeland outside of the lodge. Now, that tree is more than a reminder. It is hope that our home may one day be reclaimed.\n\nIt is the job of all rangers to defend our people wherever they live.\n\nI will be able to continue your training. Come speak to me within the lodge when you’re ready.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '你好，$N！\n\n我是鲁比纳·阳炎！我一直关注着你的壮举。你是一名出色的游侠，但我们失去家园的遭遇让你的训练显得不够完整。\n\n在二次战争期间，法斯特赛德人在小屋外种下了一颗来自我们家园的种子。如今，那棵树已不仅仅是一个提醒，它代表了我们将来夺回家园的希望。\n\n作为游侠，我们的任务是无论在哪里都要保卫我们的人民。\n\n我可以继续你的训练。当你准备好的时候，请来小屋找我谈谈。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (80227, 'Bal\'a dash, $N. You have the honor of being addressed by Magister Ala\'shor of house Sunblood.$B$BI see that you have a meager grasp of magic that exceeds the common refugee. The Magisterium these days is a shadow of what it once was. As a Magister of Quel\'Thalas, I cannot allow this to continue.$B$BWhatever may have befallen our homeland, my duties or those of the Magisterium have never ceased.$B$BCome to me and I shall make you my apprentice. If you can handle my training, you will become a capable magic caster. One worthy of a rebuilt Magisterium.$B$BSeek me out within the lodge.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '$N，我是洛萨斯·圣光之子。曾经我是白银之手骑士团的一员。\n\n在白银之手骑士团和洛丹伦王国的覆灭之前，我是一名圣骑士，是光明的勇敢仆人，无论黑暗在何处，我都会将其驱散。你的道路与我的相似。你怀揣光明的意志，同时拥有强大的战斗能力。\n\n请在小屋里找到我，我会尽我所能地训练你。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (80228, '$N, I am known as Lor\'thas the Holy. I was once part of the Order of the Silver Hand.$B$BBefore the fall of the Order and the Kingdom of Lordaeron I was known as a paladin, a valiant servant of the light, banishing darkness wherever it may be. Your path is taking you down one that is similar to mine. You carry the will of the Light alongside great martial prowess.$B$BSeek me out in the lodge and I shall train you to the best of my ability.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '愿光明与你同在，$N。\n\n我是梅拉·阳誓。\n\n我曾在奎尔萨拉斯的神殿中受命，在那里我学会了传扬太阳之光。我曾在同一间里面与高阶祭司贝洛维尔一同徜徉。\n\n可惜那些日子早已过去，我们的神殿遭受毁灭，太阳的温暖也被抛弃。\n\n我已经看到了你内心虔诚和信仰的火花。\n\n请到小屋里与我交谈。我将很愿意引导你的道路，以便有一天，我们的人民不仅能恢复对光明的信仰，还能重新寄望于我们的未来。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (80229, 'Light be with you, $N.$B$BI am Maelah Sunsworn.$B$BI was once ordained in Temples of Quel\'Thalas where I learned to preach the Light of the Sun. I walked the same halls as High Priest Belo\'vir.$B$BIt is with much sadness that those days are gone as our temples lay in ruin, and the warmth of the Sun is forsaken.$B$BI have seen the spark of devotion and faith within you.$B$BCome speak with me at the lodge. I will gladly guide your path so that, one day, our people\'s faith may be restored not only in the Light, but in our future.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '你好吗， $N. 你有幸得到太阳之血家族的魔导师阿拉绍尔称呼。\n\n我看到你对魔法的了解超过了普通难民。然而如今的魔导学会已经不再是曾经的辉煌。作为奎尔萨拉斯的魔导师，我不能任由这种情况继续下去。\n\n无论我们的家园发生了什么，我自己的职责或魔导学会的职责从未停止过。\n\n来找我，我将让你成为我的学徒。如果你能承受得住我的训练，你将成为一位出色的魔法施法者。配得上重建的主教座堂。。\n\n请在小屋里寻找我。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (80230, 'Heya, $N. I write to you because you seem like a useful asset.\n\nEveryone here will gladly boast of honor, integrity, the Sun, or other nonsense like that, but not me. I know that in order to keep our people safe, harsher methods must be used.\n\nOur people need someone to skulk in the shadows, learn things, report them, or even end threats prematurely. I sense within you an affinity for the kind of order I wish to form.\n\nSeek me out and I shall make it worth your time. I’ll be waiting for you within the lodge.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '嘿，$N。 我写信给你是因为你看起来是一个有用的资产。\n\n这里的每个人都会很高兴地夸耀荣誉、正直、太阳或其他类似的废话，但我不会。 我知道，为了保证我们人民的安全，必须使用更严厉的方法。\n\n我们的人民需要有人躲在阴影中、了解情况、报告情况，甚至提前结束威胁。 我感觉到你内心对我希望建立的那种秩序有一种亲和力。\n\n来找我吧，我会让你的时间变得值得。 我会在旅馆等你。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (80231, 'Hail to you, $N!\n\nI am Valanos Dawnfire, a swordsman of the Thalassian army.\n\nWith the fall of Quel’Thalas, my duties now involve protecting what’s left of our land, our heritage, and our people wherever they may reside.\n\nThat duty includes training new warriors who can defend our cause.\n\nSeek me out in the lodge, $N, and I shall hone your inexperienced body into that of a warrior, one that can protect the High Elves!', NULL, NULL, NULL, '向你致敬，$N！\n\n我是瓦拉诺斯·黎明火，萨拉斯军队的剑士。\n\n随着奎尔萨拉斯的陷落，我现在的职责是保护我们剩下的土地、我们的遗产和我们的人民，无论他们居住在哪里。\n\n这项职责包括培训能够捍卫我们事业的新战士。\n\n来小屋里找我吧，$N，我会把你缺乏经验的身体磨练成一名战士，一个可以保护高等精灵的战士！', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (80300, 'This is Gazztoggle\'s Report from Azshara!\n\nI have suffered many set backs in my work, my assistant Frix that I was assigned has blundered almost every task I have given him, and almost lost the Surveying Gear we were given.\n\nFrix died to the local Satyrs and the Surveying Gear was recovered from their hands, I will need a new assistant as soon as possible, and one that\'s worth my time!', NULL, NULL, NULL, '这是来自艾萨拉的加兹托格的报告！\n\n我在工作中遭受了很多挫折，我分配给我的助手弗里克斯几乎把我交给他的每项任务都搞砸了，还差点把我们分配的测量装备弄丢了。\n\n弗里克斯被当地的萨特杀死了，测量装置也从他们手中夺了回来，我需要尽快找一个新的助手，而且是一个值得我花时间的助手！', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (80301, 'Tests conducted with Ley-shards turned out completely worthless, the shards themselves around the Ruins of Eldarath are unstable and fizzle upon use.\n\nTests conducted with Essences from Ethereal\'s also proved to be lackluster.\n\nWhile they held energy, this energy was faint, and I mean, in the Gnome manner.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '使用魔网碎片进行的测试完全没有价值，位于埃达拉斯废墟周围的碎片不稳定，在使用时会发出嗤嗤声。\n\n使用虚灵精华进行的测试也被证明效果平平。\n\n虽然它们保存了能量，但这种能量非常微弱，就像侏儒的风格一样。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (80305, 'Greetings brother,\n\nI hope this letter finds you well, I am doing good in my work with the goblins of Sparkwater, I know you said my ventures were foolish but the money is great!', NULL, NULL, NULL, '你好兄弟，\n\n我希望这封信能让你一切顺利，我在火花港的地精那里做得不错，我知道你说我的冒险是愚蠢的，但是这份工作带来了很多钱！', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (80306, 'The weather of Durotar is as hot as ever and the sun beats with great strength.\n\nI am happy to hear of your success\', and wish you good fortunes.\n\nI hope to hear from you soon, let us keep in contact.\n\nRugnar.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '杜隆塔尔的天气仍然像往常一样炎热，阳光炽烈。\n\n我很高兴听到你的成功，祝愿你好运。\n\n希望很快能从你那里听到消息，让我们保持联系。\n\n鲁格纳。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (80308, 'Rugnar, your words were nice to read within the overgrowth of weeds that is the Swamp of Sorrows.\n\nI have been given leave and should be departing to Orgrimmar soon, it\'s been too long since we have last seen one another, and I am looking forward to it greatly, and have many things to tell you.\n\nYour Brother Zuul', NULL, NULL, NULL, '鲁格纳，在悲伤沼泽杂草丛生的地方读到你的话很舒服。\n\n我已经请假了，很快就要启程前往奥格瑞玛了，我们已经很久没有见面了，我对此非常期待，并且有很多事情要告诉你。\n\n你的兄弟祖尔', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (80309, 'Out of all the projects I took the only one that had any success was Skystormer Antler\'s from the local Thunderhead\'s, their energy was through the roof, and is definitely worth attempting for Sparkwater, I will send some test samples soon!\n\nReport from, Gazztoggle.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '在我参与的所有项目中，唯一取得成功的是来自当地“雷云部落”的“飞天角”项目。它们的能量爆棚，绝对值得在“闪耀之水”上尝试。我会尽快发送一些测试样本！\n\n报告人，加兹托格尔。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (80310, 'In prophecy the gods will abandon the unfaithful and break apart those that do not listen.\n\nThe world will change and the spirits shall become corrupted, and break within.\n\nThe rock shall wither, the wind shall fade, and the water shall parch, heed the warnings of the end for it is the elements themselves that need our aid.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '根据预言，众神将抛弃不忠者，并分裂那些不听劝告者。\n\n世界将发生变化，灵魂将受到污染，最终破碎。\n\n岩石将凋零，风将消失，水将干涸，要注意末日的警告，因为正是元素自身需要我们的帮助。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (80311, 'Hey boss, sorry for the late delivery, it won\'t be late again, can promise you that! I enclosed an extra bit of money for how long it took.\n\nTARLO. ', NULL, NULL, NULL, '老板，非常抱歉送货晚了，以后不会再晚，我向您保证！我在里面附上了一些额外的钱，作为时间上的补偿。\n\n塔罗。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (80320, 'To Captain Snowbeard.\n\nThe supply lines between Ironforge and Menethil harbor are being strained every day. Caravans are being attacked by the Dragonmaw orcs, and even reaching you has become a dangerous difficulty.\n\nMore help is required, and needed in dealing with the Dragonmaw menace that threatens our lands. If you have any spare soldiers, now would be the time to lend them.\n\nCaptain Stoutfist.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '致雪须船长，\n\n铁炉堡与米奈希尔港之间的补给线每天都受到压力。商队遭到龙喉兽人的袭击，甚至抵达您那里都变成了一项危险的挑战。\n\n需要更多的帮助，以及解决威胁我们土地的龙喉问题所需的支援。如果您有多余的士兵，现在正是借出他们的时候。\n\n斯托特菲斯特船长。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (80322, 'Captain Stoutfist, I am sorry to say that I cannot be of assistance. As much as the Dragonmaw is a threat to the both of us, I am severely undermanned in the mountains to be able to go on the offensive, and cannot afford to lend some of my mountaineers to your aid.\n\nI wish you the best in this matter, and I pray by Magni\'s beard that Ironforge brings aid to the both of us.\n\n Captain Snowbeard of the Ironforge Army', NULL, NULL, NULL, '斯托特菲斯特船长，很抱歉我无法提供帮助。 尽管龙喉对我们双方都构成了威胁，但我在山区的人手严重不足，无法继续进攻，而且无法借出我的一些登山者来帮助你们。\n\n我祝愿你在这件事上一切顺利，并以麦格尼的胡须祈祷铁炉堡能为我们俩带来帮助。\n\n  铁炉堡军队的雪须船长', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (80324, 'Hey there, it\'s me, Barthos, from the PAGES! I need the following for two Tilting Oscillation Inhibitors:\n\n16x Iron Bar\n6x Strong Flux\n2x Bronze Whirring Gizmo\n2x Fused Wiring', NULL, NULL, NULL, '嘿，是我，巴托斯，我需要以下材料来制作两个倾斜振荡抑制器：\n\n16块铁锭\n6份强效助熔剂\n2个青铜嗡嗡装置\n2捆熔化的导线', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (80325, 'This should be all that is needed!\n\nGood luck in your searching, and be quick. There is much to do!\n\nBarthos Thundercrack, Engineering Legend of Hawk\'s Vigil', NULL, NULL, NULL, '这就是所需的全部材料！\n\n祝你在寻找过程中好运，而且要快点。任务繁重！\n\n鹰眼哨站的工程传奇，巴索斯·雷霹。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (80326, 'Barthos, if the senate finds out about all these supplies heading to Hawk\'s Vigil they are going to be furious. The expenses of the Airport are quite large after all! Be sure that the supplies I have sent you last as long as possible before asking for more.\n\nYour friend, Orion Coalborn', NULL, NULL, NULL, '巴索斯，如果议会发现所有这些供应品都被运到了鹰眼哨站，他们会非常愤怒的。毕竟，机场的开支相当大！确保我送给你的这些供应品在尽可能长的时间内足够使用，然后再考虑是否需要更多。\n\n你的朋友，奥里恩·煤胎。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (80327, 'To Duke Ramon III,\n\nThanks again for everything you\'ve done. For my own safety, I had to keep my head low since I left Stormwind.\n\nIt appears that SI:7 has been keeping tabs on me, but I assure you that I have kept myself unseen so far and well-hidden within my room.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '致拉蒙三世公爵，\n\n再次感谢您所做的一切。为了我的安全，自从我离开暴风城以来，我不得不保持低调。\n\n似乎军情七处一直在监视着我，但我向您保证，到目前为止我一直保持不被察觉，并且很好地藏匿在我的房间里。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (80328, 'Your support has been instrumental and has saved my life from that wretched stockade.\n\nMy uncle would have been proud to have called you a great friend, I hope to hear from you soon, I am unsure of when I will be leaving this place\n\nA friend, Martin Corinth', NULL, NULL, NULL, '您的支持至关重要，使我摆脱了那个悲惨的寨子。\n\n我的叔叔会为能称您为一位伟大的朋友而感到自豪，我希望很快能从您那里听到消息，我不确定我何时会离开这个地方。\n\n一位朋友，马丁·科林斯。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (80329, 'Dear Lord Commander Ryke\n\nI have entrusted the bearer of this envelope to deliver this message.\n\nThe man of whom you are investigating, Harlus Ashbuckle, is operating under a false name, his real name is that of Martin Corinth who hailed from Lordaeron and escaped at the onset of the Third War.\n\nMartin was from a rich family and had many connections to the nobility in Stormwind.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '亲爱的指挥官莱克大人，\n\n我已委托此信封的持有者将此信息交付。\n\n您正在调查的人，哈勒斯·艾什巴克尔，是使用假名行事的，他的真名是马丁·科林斯，他来自洛丹伦，于第三次战争爆发时逃脱。\n\n马丁来自一个富有的家庭，并与暴风城的贵族有许多联系。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (80330, 'One such connection saved Martin from being executed in Stormwind for both the murder of innocents, and practicing forbidden magic.\n\nIf there is a foul magic that plagues Hawk\'s Vigil I would have it under my suspicion that he is responsible.\n\nMartin Corinth, upon being exiled from Stormwind as was the \'terms\' of his release from imprisonment, was to abandon the dark arts within all realms held by the Alliance.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '正是这样的联系使马丁免于因谋杀无辜和使用禁忌魔法而在暴风城被处决。\n\n如果有一种邪恶的魔法困扰着鹰眼哨站的守夜者，我会怀疑他对此负有责任。\n\n马丁·科林斯在被从暴风城放逐（这是他出狱的“条件”）后，将放弃联盟所掌握的所有领域内的黑暗魔法。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (80331, 'I give you the judication of Stormwind to dispense justice to this man, it has been a long time coming.\n\nFree your lands of any darkness that he may eventually bring to it.\n\nMaster Mathias Shaw, Leader of the SI:7', NULL, NULL, NULL, '我将赋予您暴风城的裁决权，以向这个人施以公正的制裁，这是早就应该做的事情。\n\n让您的领土远离他可能带来的一切黑暗。\n\n大师马修斯·肖，军情七处领袖。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (1000063, 'The spectators want to see real battles! Don\'t rig them!', NULL, NULL, NULL, '观众想要看到真正的战斗！不要操纵比赛！', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (1000243, 'THE CRUSADES WALL AGAINST THE SCOURGE\n\nPaladin of the Scarlet Crusade, Knight of the Silver Hand, Served with honor in the wars against our enemies.\n\nThere has never been a man more fearless or tenacious in his duties, your virtue is something that all of the crusade look up to in inspiration, and your judgement will never be forgotten.\n\nYou were the fist of our kin, and the wall that kept evil at bay.\n\nMay the light guide you to your new beginning with the same fury you once held in life.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '十字军对抗天灾之墙\n\n血色十字军的圣骑士，银色之手的骑士，在对抗敌人的战争中光荣地服役。\n\n从未有人像您一样无所畏惧，坚守职责，您的品德是所有十字军所仰望的灵感之源，您的判断将永远被铭记。\n\n您曾是我们同胞的拳头，那道阻止邪恶前行的墙。\n\n愿圣光引领您以与生前同样的热情踏上新的征程。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (1000244, 'The Vow of the Initiate\n\nI will give my service unto the Crusade, and pledge my life to its cause, I shall obey without question, I shall answer the call for my people.\n\nThe Vow of the Crusader\n\nIt is my creed to defend the lands of my people, for Lordaeron is the Crusade, and the Crusade is Lordaeron. I shall dispense justice to all those that wrong my brothers and sisters in arms. I am the embodiment of what once was.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '入会者的誓言\n\n我将为十字军东征服务，并保证我的生命为其事业，我将毫无疑问地服从，我将响应我人民的号召。\n\n十字军的誓言\n\n捍卫我人民的土地是我的信条，因为洛丹伦即是十字军，而十字军即是洛丹伦。我将对所有冒犯我战友的人施以公正。我是曾经存在的化身。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (1000245, 'The Vow of the Knight\n\nThat which is noble, I shall uphold.\nThat what is tainted, I will destroy.\nThat which is sacred, I will protect.\n\nTo my brothers, and my sisters this oath be true.\n\nThe Vow of the Missionary\n\nTo the ways of old is the charge of my kind, to preserve the ways and traditions of the holy church, and to sanctify and bless our armaments in this holy war. To purge the deceivers, the heretics and the unfaithful is my cause.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '骑士的誓言\n\n我将维护高贵之物。\n我将毁灭腐化之物。\n我将保护神圣之物。\n\n对于我的兄弟姐妹，此誓言永真。\n\n传教士的誓言\n\n对于我种族的传承，是我责无旁贷的使命，保护圣教的方式和传统，并在这场神圣的战争中神圣化和祝福我们的武器。清除欺骗者、异端和不忠者，是我的使命。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (1000246, 'The Light, it is our protector within these decrepit and plagued lands, once so full of life and beauty has now been reduced to decay. We are a torch within the darkness, and the Light is what holds it back. It is the shining example of what was, and what will be in the new Lordaeron that we will create in its path. The Paladins, and the Priests of our order wield its greatness with devastating effect, as many brother, and sister has seen. \n\nIt is within the Light we should place our hopes, our prayers, and our trust.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '光明，在这些破败和受瘟疫蹂躏的土地中，它是我们的守护者，曾经充满生机和美丽的土地现在已经变成了腐朽。我们是黑暗中的火炬，而光明是阻止黑暗的力量。它是曾经和未来洛丹伦的光辉典范，我们将在其道路上创造。圣骑士和我们教团的牧师们用它的伟大带来了毁灭性的影响，正如许多兄弟姐妹所看到的那样。\n\n我们应该将希望、祈祷和信任寄托在圣光之中。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (1000247, 'A beacon that connected the creation of this order, and still keeps us together now, even after so much hardship, and trial. Despite how many times we have come close to ruin, and despite the fall of the kingdom around us we stand firm. \n\nShould the time come when darkness encroaches,', NULL, NULL, NULL, '作为这个秩序的创立者，它是我们的信标，现在仍然将我们紧密相连，尽管经历了如此多的困难和考验。尽管我们多次陷入毁灭的边缘，尽管我们周围的王国已经倒塌，我们仍然坚定不移地站立。\n\n如果黑暗逼近的时刻到来，', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (1000248, 'remember that the Light always shines through you, and your sacrifice will be repaid fully in the Light\'s graces.\n\nThe Light does not forsake, the Light does not forget. Let us forever keep it at our hearts.\n\nNo matter how dark the world is, the Light will always shine again.\n\n~Scribe Dafoldt', NULL, NULL, NULL, '请记住，圣光始终闪耀在你身上，你的牺牲将在圣光的恩典中得到充分的回报。\n\n圣光不会放弃，圣光不会忘记。 让我们永远把它记在心里。\n\n无论世界多么黑暗，光明总会再次闪耀。\n\n~抄写员达福德', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `locales_page_text` VALUES (1772030, 'Grim Batol Memorial\n\n\nA shrine dedicated to those that fought, and gave their lives in the defence of innocents against our greatest of challenges. May this shrine forever honor those that died within our once great halls in defiance against our invaders.\n\nYou shall never be forgotten.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '格瑞姆巴托纪念碑\n\n一个神龛，献给那些在保护无辜者免受我们最大的挑战时英勇战斗并献出生命的人们。愿这座神龛永远纪念那些在我们曾经伟大的大厅内，以抵抗侵略者的姿态而去世的人们。\n\n你们永远不会被遗忘。', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
